美國與大多數已開發國家不同，並沒有單一的醫療保險系統。<ref name="IOM 2004">{{cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/insuringamericas00inst/page/25|title=Insuring America's health: principles and recommendations|author=Institute of Medicine. Committee on the Consequences of Uninsurance|date=2004-01-13|publisher=National Academies Press|isbn=978-0-309-52826-9|location=Washington, DC|page=[https://archive.org/details/insuringamericas00inst/page/25 25]}}</ref>而是大多數人都利用私人保險以及各種聯邦和州的保險計劃來覆蓋。<ref>Access to health care in America. Institute of Medicine, Committee on Monitoring Access to Personal Health Care Services. Millman M, editor. Washington: National Academies Press; 1993.</ref>截至2017年，最普遍的是透過雇主的團體保險計劃而取得，覆蓋人數達到1.5億。<ref name=":11">{{Cite web|url=https://www.commonwealthfund.org/blog/2017/decline-employer-sponsored-health-insurance|title=The Decline of Employer-Sponsored Health Insurance|website=commonwealthfund.org|language=en|access-date=2018-11-25|archive-date=2020-03-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200330201758/https://www.commonwealthfund.org/blog/2017/decline-employer-sponsored-health-insurance|dead-url=no}}</ref>其他主要來源有：覆蓋7,000萬人的Medicaid，覆蓋5,000萬人的Medicare，和由《PPACA》建立的[[醫療保險市集|醫療保險市集]]，覆蓋約1,700萬人。<ref name=":11" />在2017年所做的一項研究發現，醫療保險市集裡面提供的計劃中有73％，由於網絡狹窄，人們在接洽和選擇供應商的時候會受到限制。<ref name=":11" />
 
由{{link-en|全國衛生統計中心|National Center for Health Statistics}}設計的{{link-en|全國健康訪談調查|National Health Interview Survey }}，跟踪可及性和可負擔性方面的項目，包括有：擁有保險人口的佔比、擁有常規的醫療護理、每年訪視牙醫、可預防的住院比率、無法看專科醫生問題的報告、因費用而延誤就醫、醫療保險覆蓋的成本。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cdc.gov/nchs/nhis.htm|title=National Center for Health Statistics|website=Cdc.gov|access-date=2016-12-01|archive-date=2020-03-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200330201800/https://www.cdc.gov/nchs/nhis.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>在2004年，OECD的一份報告指出："到1990年，所有OECD國家（[[墨西哥|墨西哥]]、[[土耳其|土耳其]]、和美國除外）都實現全民，或者幾乎全民（至少有98.4％的參保）的健保 "。<ref name="Docteur 2004">{{cite book |chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=r6MLakbHnEQC&pg=PA74 |title=Towards high-performing health systems: policy studies |last1=Docteur |first1=Elizabeth |last2=Oxley |first2=Howard |name-list-format=vanc |date=2004-10-19 |publisher=OECD |isbn=978-92-64-01559-3 |series=The OECD health project |location=Paris |pages=25, 74 |chapter=Health-system reform: lessons from experience |access-date=2020-09-04 |archive-date=2020-12-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201207143351/https://books.google.com/books?id=r6MLakbHnEQC&pg=PA74 |dead-url=no }}</ref>在 2004年，[[美國國家醫學院|美國國家醫學院]]的報告還指出，"由於缺乏醫療保險，美國每年大約會發生18,000例不必要的死亡。"<ref name="IOM 2004" />
 
[[蓋洛普|蓋洛普]]從2008年開始追踪無醫療保險的美國成年人的佔比。在PPACA強制執行之前，這種比率在2013年達到18.0％的高峰，在2016年第三季度下降到10.9％，在2018年第四季度回升為13.7％。<ref name=WittersJan2019>{{cite news |url=https://news.gallup.com/poll/246134/uninsured-rate-rises-four-year-high.aspx |title=U.S. Uninsured Rate Rises to Four-Year High |first=Dan |last=Witters |name-list-format=vanc |date=2019-01-23 |newspaper=Gallup News: Well-being |access-date=2019-08-13 |archive-date=2020-03-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200330201733/https://news.gallup.com/poll/246134/uninsured-rate-rises-four-year-high.aspx |dead-url=no }}</ref> "自低點往上增加2.8個百分點，表示無醫療保險的成年人淨增加約700萬人。"<ref name=WittersJan2019 />
 
[[美國普查局|美國普查局]]報告說，在2017年無醫療保險的人數為2,850萬人（8.8％），<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/library/publications/2018/demo/p60-264.html|title=Health Insurance Coverage in the United States: 2017|last=Bureau|first=US Census|website=census.gov|language=en-US|access-date=2018-11-25|archive-date=2021-02-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210205024239/https://www.census.gov/library/publications/2018/demo/p60-264.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>比2010年的4,990萬人（16.3％）有所下降。<ref name="DeNavas-Walt 2011">{{cite book|url=https://www.census.gov/prod/2011pubs/p60-239.pdf|title=Income, poverty, and health insurance coverage in the United States: 2010|last1=DeNavas-Walt|first1=Carmen|last2=Proctor|first2=Bernadette D.|last3=Smith|first3=Jessica C.|name-list-format=vanc|date=2011-09-13|publisher=U.S. Government Printing Office|series=U.S. Census Bureau: Current Population Reports, P60-239|location=Washington, DC|access-date=2020-09-04|archive-date=2021-01-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210122125911/https://www.census.gov/prod/2011pubs/p60-239.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="uninsured 2009">{{cite news|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052748704394704575496093363948142|title=Recession swells number of uninsured to 50.7 million|author=Johnson, Avery|date=2010-09-17|newspaper=The Wall Street Journal|access-date=2010-11-21|page=A4|archive-date=2020-12-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201207143441/https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052748704394704575496093363948142|dead-url=no}} * {{cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/news/nation/2010-09-17-uninsured17_ST_N.htm|title=Number of uninsured Americans rises to 50.7 million|last=Wolf|first=Richard|name-list-format=vanc|date=2010-09-17|newspaper=USA Today|access-date=2010-11-21|page=8A|archive-date=2012-06-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120627074536/http://www.usatoday.com/news/nation/2010-09-17-uninsured17_ST_N.htm|dead-url=no}}
