===醫療產品以及研發===
美國與大多數國家一樣，[[藥品|藥品]]和[[醫療器械|醫療器械]]的製造和生產是由私人公司來從事。而醫療器械和藥品的研發則由公共和私人經費共同支持。 2003年，美國在此的研發支出約為950億美元，其中400億美元由公家支付，550億美元由私人機構支付。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.csic.es/vri/otros-programas/esf/EMRC_Whitepaper.pdf|title=(Open using Adobe reader) p. 16|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091004085517/http://www.csic.es/vri/otros-programas/esf/EMRC_Whitepaper.pdf|archive-date=2009-10-04|accessdate=2020-09-04|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Medical Research Spending Doubled Over Past Decade">[http://www.medpagetoday.com/PublicHealthPolicy/HealthPolicy/tb/1767 Medical Research Spending Doubled Over Past Decade] {{Wayback|url=http://www.medpagetoday.com/PublicHealthPolicy/HealthPolicy/tb/1767 |date=20070414132617 }}, Neil Osterweil, MedPage Today, September 20, 2005</ref>由於這些投資，美國在醫療創新方面，無論是從收入還是在引入新藥和新器械的數量上，都享有世界領先地位。<ref name="EFPIA">{{cite web|url=http://www.efpia.org/content/Default.asp?PageID=388|title=Improving Europe's competitiveness|publisher=[[European_Federation_of_Pharmaceutical_Industries_and_Associations|EFPIA]]|access-date=2016-11-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090823030103/http://www.efpia.org/content/Default.asp?PageID=388|archive-date=2009-08-23|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref name="Europe">Stats from 2007 Europ.Fed.of Pharm.Indust.and Assoc. Retrieved June 17, 2009, from [http://212.3.246.100/Objects/2/Files/infigures2007.pdf]{{dead link|date=October 2017|bot=InternetArchiveBot|fix-attempted=yes}}</ref>2016年，美國藥廠的研發支出估計約為590億美元。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.statista.com/statistics/265085/research-and-development-expenditure-us-pharmaceutical-industry/#0|title=U.S. pharmaceutical R&D expenditure 1995-2015 {{!}} Statistic|website=Statista|language=en|access-date=2018-02-28|archive-date=2020-12-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201212010734/https://www.statista.com/statistics/265085/research-and-development-expenditure-us-pharmaceutical-industry/|dead-url=no}}</ref>2006年，美國在[[生物技術|生物技術]]的收入佔全世界的的四分之三，而在生物技術的研發支出，佔全世界的82％。<ref name="EFPIA" /><ref name="Europe" />根據多個國際藥品產業組織的說法，美國專利藥品的高昂價格，促進對此類研究和開發的不斷投資。<ref name="EFPIA" /><ref name="Europe" /> <ref name="PHRMA">{{cite web |url=http://www.phrma.org/files/PhRMA_annualreportFianl.pdf |title=2008 Annual Report |access-date=2009-06-20 |work=PHRMA |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081230124209/http://www.phrma.org/files/PhRMA_annualreportFianl.pdf |archive-date=2008-12-30 |dead-url=no }}</ref>PPACA會迫使[[製藥產業|製藥產業]]以較便宜的價格出售他們的產品。<ref name="Houlton 2012 23">{{cite journal|last=Houlton|first=Sarah| name-list-format = vanc |title=Debating Obamacare|journal=Chemistry and Industry|date=September 2012|volume=76|page=23|doi=10.1002/cind.7609_5.x|issue=9}}</ref> 因此，這個產業的投資預算有可能會因此降低。<ref name="Houlton 2012 23" />

===醫療衛生提供者的業務===
美國正在進行中的人口結構轉變，會因為需要更多的護理，而對醫療系統有更大的需求，由於"{{link-en|嬰兒潮時期出生的人|Baby Boomers}}"正進入退休年齡<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/fact-checker/wp/2014/07/24/do-10000-baby-boomers-retire-every-day/|title=Do 10,000 baby boomers retire every day?|last=Kessler|first=Glenn|name-list-format=vanc|date=2014-07-24|work=Washington Post|access-date=2019-11-10|language=en-US|issn=0190-8286|archive-date=2021-01-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210125111931/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/fact-checker/wp/2014/07/24/do-10000-baby-boomers-retire-every-day/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，預計這些老年人口將讓全國的醫療費用增加5％，甚至更多<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.economist.com/news/2014/11/13/health-care?zid=318&ah=ac379c09c1c3fb67e0e8fd1964d5247f|title=Health Care|date=2014-11-13|work=The Economist|access-date=2019-11-10|issn=0013-0613|archive-date=2020-12-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201207143828/https://www.economist.com/news/2014/11/13/health-care?zid=318&ah=ac379c09c1c3fb67e0e8fd1964d5247f|dead-url=no}}</ref>。自1990年代後期以來，醫療衛生的總支出一直在增加，支出率的增長速度快過通貨膨脹率，不僅是由於價格上漲的原因而已。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.healthsystemtracker.org/chart-collection/u-s-spending-healthcare-changed-time/|title=How has U.S. spending on healthcare changed over time?|website=Peterson-Kaiser Health System Tracker|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-11|archive-date=2021-01-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210127210855/https://www.healthsystemtracker.org/chart-collection/u-s-spending-healthcare-changed-time/|dead-url=no}}</ref>此外，在45歲以上人群的支出已是45歲以下人群支出的8.3倍。<ref>{{Cite journal|vauthors=Prowle MJ, Araali NA|title=Meeting The Escalating Demands For Health And Social Care Services Of Elderly Populations In Developing Countries: A Strategic Perspective|journal=American Journal of Medical Research|language=en-gb|volume=4|issue=2|pages=127|doi=10.22381/ajmr4220175|year=2017|url=http://eprints.glos.ac.uk/4723/1/costs%20of%20ageing.pdf|access-date=2020-09-04|archive-date=2020-12-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201207143818/http://eprints.glos.ac.uk/4723/1/costs%20of%20ageing.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>
 
===替代醫學===
與以前相比，其他的{{link-en|醫療方式|therapy}}目前較常被使用。這個領域被稱為[[替代醫學|替代醫學]]（Complementary and Alternative Medicine，CAM），並且被定義為通常沒在醫學院教授，或是沒在醫院中採用的療法。包括[[草藥醫學|草藥醫學]]、[[按摩|按摩]]、{{link-en|能量治療醫學|energy medicine}}、[[順勢療法|順勢療法]]、以及最近開始流行的[[冷療|冷療]]、[[拔罐|拔罐]]療法、和{{link-en|穿顱磁刺激儀|Transcranial magnetic stimulation}}（TMS）療法。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thespectrum.com/story/news/2019/10/06/cryotherapy-cupping-new-alternative-medicine-now-st-george/3450970002/|title=Cryotherapy, cupping and TMS: New forms of alternative medicine treatment in St. George|last=Wilkins|first=Terell| name-list-format = vanc |website=The Spectrum & Daily News|language=en|access-date=2019-11-11}}</ref>這類CAM的提供者在美國有時會被認定是合法的醫療衛生提供者。<ref>{{Cite web|title=29 CFR § 825.125 - Definition of health care provider.|url=https://www.law.cornell.edu/cfr/text/29/825.125|access-date=2020-11-13|website=LII / Legal Information Institute|language=en|archive-date=2021-10-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211008032716/https://www.law.cornell.edu/cfr/text/29/825.125|dead-url=no}}</ref>一般會採用這些替代治療方法的原因，包括用來改善患者健康狀況、涉入變革性的經歷、對自己的健康有更多控制、或者是尋求更好的方法來緩解慢性疾病的症狀。他們的目標不僅是治療肉體上的疾病，還可解決潛在的營養、社會、情感、和精神上的病因。在2008年所做的一項調查發現，美國有37％的醫院至少提供一種形式的CAM治療，主要原因是由於患者的需求（在84％的醫院）。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.aha.org/presscenter/pressrel/2008/080915-pr-cam.shtml|title=Latest Survey Shows More Hospitals Offering Complementary and Alternative Medicine Services|date=2012-09-02|access-date=2019-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120902072431/http://www.aha.org/presscenter/pressrel/2008/080915-pr-cam.shtml|archive-date=2012-09-02|dead-url=no}}</ref>根據2007年的統計分析，CAM治療的平均費用為33.9美元，其中三分之二是由[[自付費用|自付費用]]支付。<ref name=":13">{{cite web |url=https://nccih.nih.gov/news/camstats/costs/costdatafs.htm |title=The Use of Complementary and Alternative Medicine in the United States: Cost Data |website=NCCIH |language=en |access-date=2019-11-11 |archive-date=2020-02-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200209082050/https://nccih.nih.gov/news/camstats/costs/costdatafs.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>此外，CAM治療佔醫療衛生總費用的11.2％<ref name=":13" />。在2002年至2008年期間，患者CAM的支出呈上升趨勢，但此後則穩定維持在約40％的成年人會使用。<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Davis MA, Martin BI, Coulter ID, Weeks WB | title = US spending on complementary and alternative medicine during 2002-08 plateaued, suggesting role in reformed health system | journal = Health Affairs | volume = 32 | issue = 1 | pages = 45–52 | date = January 2013 | pmid = 23297270 | pmc = 3644505 | doi = 10.1377/hlthaff.2011.0321 }}</ref>

