美國醫療衛生支出總額佔GDP的百分比高於類似的高所得國家，這可由服務本身的價格上漲，管理系統的成本高過別國，或者使用更多的服務等因素的綜合來解釋。<ref name="Marmoretal2009">{{cite journal | vauthors = Marmor T, Oberlander J, White J | title = The Obama administration's options for health care cost control: hope versus reality | journal = Annals of Internal Medicine | volume = 150 | issue = 7 | pages = 485–9 | date = April 2009 | pmid = 19258549 | pmc =  | doi = 10.7326/0003-4819-150-7-200904070-00114 | doi-access = free }}[http://www.annals.org/content/150/7/485.full Free full-text] {{Wayback|url=http://www.annals.org/content/150/7/485.full |date=20120415031823 }}.</ref>醫療衛生費用的增長速度遠快於通貨膨脹，一直是驅策應對醫療衛生改革的動力。截至2016年，美國共花費3.3兆美元（佔GDP的17.9％），或人均支出10,438美元; 主要類別是32％的醫院護理，20％的醫生和臨床服務，以及10％的處方藥。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cms.gov/Research-Statistics-Data-and-Systems/Statistics-Trends-and-Reports/NationalHealthExpendData/downloads/highlights.pdf|title=National Health Expenditures 2016 Highlights|date=|website=|access-date=|archive-date=2019-10-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191008145249/https://www.cms.gov/Research-Statistics-Data-and-Systems/Statistics-Trends-and-Reports/NationalHealthExpendData/downloads/highlights.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>相較之下，英國人均花費僅僅3,749美元而已。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.npr.org/sections/goatsandsoda/2017/04/20/524774195/what-country-spends-the-most-and-least-on-health-care-per-person|title=What Country Spends The Most (And Least) On Health Care Per Person?|work=NPR.org|access-date=2018-02-28|language=en|archive-date=2020-12-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201225033950/https://www.npr.org/sections/goatsandsoda/2017/04/20/524774195/what-country-spends-the-most-and-least-on-health-care-per-person|dead-url=no}}</ref>
 
在2018年所做的的一項分析，結論是價格和行政管理成本兩項是造成高成本的主要原因，其中包括人工、藥品、和診斷的價格。<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Papanicolas I, Woskie LR, Jha AK | title = Health Care Spending in the United States and Other High-Income Countries | journal = JAMA | volume = 319 | issue = 10 | pages = 1024–1039 | date = March 2018 | pmid = 29536101 | doi = 10.1001/jama.2018.1150 | s2cid = 4293977 | url = http://eprints.lse.ac.uk/87362/2/jama_Papanicolas_2018_sc_180001_3_.pdf | lay-url = http://www.wbur.org/commonhealth/2018/03/13/us-health-costs-high-jha | lay-source = WBUR | access-date = 2020-09-04 | archive-date = 2020-11-04 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201104141404/http://eprints.lse.ac.uk/87362/2/jama_Papanicolas_2018_sc_180001_3_.pdf | dead-url = no }}</ref>高價格和高使用數量的結合會導致特殊的支出；在美國，高利潤的手術，包括[[血管再成形術|血管再成形術]]、[[剖宮產|剖腹產]]、{{link-en|膝關節置換|Knee replacement}}、以及[[X射線電腦斷層掃描|CT掃描]]、和[[核磁共振成像|MRI掃描]]被大量使用；尤其是CT掃描和MRI掃描，在美國都顯示出更高的使用率。<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Emanuel EJ | title = The Real Cost of the US Health Care System | journal = JAMA | volume = 319 | issue = 10 | pages = 983–985 | date = March 2018 | pmid = 29536081 | doi = 10.1001/jama.2018.1151 }}</ref>
 
2011年，美國住院總費用為3,873億美元，自1997年以來（經過通膨指數調整後）增長63％。自1997年以來，每次住院費用增長47％，在2011年的平均數為10,000美元。<ref name="hcup-us.ahrq.gov">Pfuntner A., Wier L.M., Elixhauser A. Overview of Hospital Stays in the United States, 2011. HCUP Statistical Brief #166. November 2013. Agency for Healthcare Research and Quality, Rockville, MD. [http://www.hcup-us.ahrq.gov/reports/statbriefs/sb166.jsp] {{Wayback|url=http://www.hcup-us.ahrq.gov/reports/statbriefs/sb166.jsp |date=20191110230344 }}.</ref>截至2008年，美國醫療衛生支出中，公共支出佔45％至56％之間。<ref name="content.healthaffairs.org">Thomas M. Selden and Merrile Sing, [http://content.healthaffairs.org/cgi/reprint/hlthaff.27.5.w349v1 "The Distribution Of Public Spending For Health Care In The United States, 2002,"] {{Wayback|url=http://content.healthaffairs.org/cgi/reprint/hlthaff.27.5.w349v1 |date=20090908040822 }} [[Health_Affairs|Health Affairs]] 27, no. 5 (2008): w349–59 (published online July 29, 2008)</ref>從2003年至2011年，外科手術、傷害、以及孕產婦、和嬰兒保健就診費用每年增加2％以上。此外，雖然平均住院日數維持穩定，但住院費用從2003年的9,100美元增加到2011年的10,600美元，當初預計到2013年將達到11,000美元。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hcup-us.ahrq.gov/reports/statbriefs/sb175-Hospital-Cost-Utilization-Projections-2013.jsp|title=Trends and Projections in Inpatient Hospital Costs and Utilization, 2003–2013|date=July 2014|work=HCUP Statistical Brief #175|publisher=Agency for Healthcare Research and Quality|location=Rockville, MD|vauthors=Weiss AJ, Barrett ML, Steiner CA|accessdate=2020-09-04|archive-date=2019-03-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190329172602/https://www.hcup-us.ahrq.gov/reports/statbriefs/sb175-Hospital-Cost-Utilization-Projections-2013.jsp|dead-url=no}}</ref>2018年的人均費用為11,172美元。<ref name="#1">{{Cite web |url=https://www.cms.gov/Research-Statistics-Data-and-Systems/Statistics-Trends-and-Reports/NationalHealthExpendData/NationalHealthAccountsHistorical |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2020-09-04 |archive-date=2019-11-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191111221743/https://www.cms.gov/Research-Statistics-Data-and-Systems/Statistics-Trends-and-Reports/NationalHealthExpendData/NationalHealthAccountsHistorical.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>
 
根據WHO的數據，2011年美國的醫療衛生總支出佔GDP的18％，居世界之首。<ref name="WHO 2011">{{cite book|url=http://www.who.int/gho/publications/world_health_statistics/2011/en/index.html|title=World health statistics 2011|author=WHO|publisher=World Health Organization|year=2011|isbn=978-92-4-156419-9|location=Geneva|access-date=2020-09-04|archive-date=2014-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140130191107/http://www.who.int/gho/publications/world_health_statistics/2011/en/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[美國衛生及公共服務部|美國衛生及公共服務部]]（HHS）預計，醫療衛生支出佔GDP的比例維持上升的趨勢，到2017年會達到GDP的19％（2018年實際的GDP佔比為17.7%<ref name="#1"/>）。<ref name="NHE Fact Sheet">[http://www.cms.hhs.gov/NationalHealthExpendData/25_NHE_Fact_Sheet.asp#TopOfPage "National Health Expenditure Data: NHE Fact Sheet,"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cms.hhs.gov/NationalHealthExpendData/25_NHE_Fact_Sheet.asp#TopOfPage |date=20100304074934 }} [[Centers_for_Medicare_and_Medicaid_Services|Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services]], referenced February 26, 2008</ref><ref>Sean Keehan, Andrea Sisko, Christopher Truffer, Sheila Smith, Cathy Cowan, John Poisal, M. Kent Clemens, and the National Health Expenditure Accounts Projections Team, [http://content.healthaffairs.org/cgi/reprint/hlthaff.27.2.w145v1 "Health Spending Projections Through 2017: The Baby-Boom Generation Is Coming To Medicare"] {{Wayback|url=http://content.healthaffairs.org/cgi/reprint/hlthaff.27.2.w145v1 |date=20100417224453 }}, ''Health Affairs'' Web Exclusive, February 26, 2008. Retrieved February 27, 2008.</ref>在美國，每一美元的醫療衛生費用中，分佈的方式：31％用於醫院護理、21％用於醫師/臨床服務、10％用於藥品、4％用於牙科、6％用於療養院、和3％用於家庭醫療衛生、3％的其他零售產品、3％的政府公共衛生活動、7%的行政管理費用、7%的投資、6%的其他專業服務（[[物理治療|物理治療]]師，[[視光學|驗光]]師等）。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kaiseredu.org/Issue-Modules/US-Health-Care-Costs/Background-Brief.aspx#How%20is%20the%20U.S.%20health%20care%20dollar%20spent |title=Health Costs |publisher=The Henry J. Kaiser Family Foundation |website=Kaiseredu.org |date=2016-10-03 |access-date=2016-12-01 |archive-date=2013-09-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130910181724/http://www.kaiseredu.org/Issue-Modules/US-Health-Care-Costs/Background-Brief.aspx#How%20is%20the%20U.S.%20health%20care%20dollar%20spent |dead-url=no }}</ref>
 
在2017年所做的一項研究，估計將近一半的醫院護理和急診室服務有關聯。<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Marcozzi D, Carr B, Liferidge A, Baehr N, Browne B | title = Trends in the Contribution of Emergency Departments to the Provision of Hospital-Associated Health Care in the USA | journal = International Journal of Health Services | volume = 48 | issue = 2 | pages = 267–288 | date = April 2018 | pmid = 29039720 | doi = 10.1177/0020731417734498 | s2cid = 206411788 | lay-url = https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2017/10/171017091849.htm | access-date = 2020-09-04 | archive-date = 2020-12-07 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201207143932/https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2017/10/171017091849.htm | dead-url = no }}</ref>在2017年，對在2009-2011年之間的數據作分析，在患者生命的最後一年的{{link-en|臨終護理|end-of-life care}}的花費約佔8.5％，生命的最後三年的花費約佔16.7％。<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = French EB, McCauley J, Aragon M, Bakx P, Chalkley M, Chen SH, Christensen BJ, Chuang H, Côté-Sergent A, De Nardi M, Fan E, Échevin D, Geoffard PY, Gastaldi-Ménager C, Gørtz M, Ibuka Y, Jones JB, Kallestrup-Lamb M, Karlsson M, Klein TJ, de Lagasnerie G, Michaud PC, O'Donnell O, Rice N, Skinner JS, van Doorslaer E, Ziebarth NR, Kelly E | display-authors = 6 | title = End-Of-Life Medical Spending In Last Twelve Months Of Life Is Lower Than Previously Reported | journal = Health Affairs | volume = 36 | issue = 7 | pages = 1211–1217 | date = July 2017 | pmid = 28679807 | doi = 10.1377/hlthaff.2017.0174 | url = http://discovery.ucl.ac.uk/1567490/1/De%20Nardi_French_etal_round3_v4.pdf | access-date = 2020-09-04 | archive-date = 2019-04-28 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190428024416/http://discovery.ucl.ac.uk/1567490/1/De%20Nardi_French_etal_round3_v4.pdf | dead-url = no }}</ref>
 
截至2013年，醫療衛生相關的行政管理費用占美國醫療衛生總費用的30％。<ref>{{cite news |last=Pfeffer |first=Jeffrey |name-list-format=vanc |agency= |title=The Reason Health Care Is So Expensive: Insurance Companies |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/bw/articles/2013-04-10/the-reason-health-care-is-so-expensive-insurance-companies |quote= |newspaper=[[Bloomberg_News|Bloomberg News]] |date=2013-04-10 |access-date=2016-01-17 |archive-date=2016-01-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160131050101/http://www.bloomberg.com/bw/articles/2013-04-10/the-reason-health-care-is-so-expensive-insurance-companies |dead-url=no }}</ref>
  
自由市場的擁護者聲稱醫療衛生系統為"功能失調"，因為支付費用是由保險公司以第三方的身份來執行，雖然患者是財務和醫療選擇的主要參與者，卻不能發揮影響。[[加圖研究所|加圖研究所]]聲稱，由於政府的干預，產生諸如Medicare和Medicaid之類的計劃，增進保險的可得性，因此把這個問題加劇。<ref>Liebowitz, Stan [http://www.cato.org/pubs/pas/pa211.html Policy Analysis: Why Health Care Costs So Much] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cato.org/pubs/pas/pa211.html |date=20161027001650 }}, Cato Institute, June 23, 1994</ref>根據一項由{{link-en|美國健康保險計劃|America's Health Insurance Plans}}（一家在[[華盛頓哥倫比亞特區|華盛頓哥倫比亞特區]]為醫療保險業服務的[[遊說團體|遊說]]公司，也是美國醫療保險產業協會）委託[[普華永道|普華永道]]會計師事務所及管理顧問公司所做的研究，利用率的提高是美國醫療衛生成本上升的主要驅動力。<ref name="PWC">[http://www.ahipbelieves.com/media/The%20Factors%20Fueling%20Rising%20Healthcare%20Costs.pdf The Factors Fueling Rising Healthcare Costs 2006] {{Wayback|url=http://www.ahipbelieves.com/media/The%20Factors%20Fueling%20Rising%20Healthcare%20Costs.pdf |date=20071127151147 }}, PriceWaterhouseCoopers for America's Health Insurance Plans, 2006. Retrieved October 8, 2007.</ref>這項研究列舉導致利用率提高的各項原因，包括：消費者需求增加、新療法出現、更密集的診斷測試、生活風格因素、轉用更廣泛適用的計劃、以及價格更高昂的技術。<ref name="PWC" />這項研究還提到把費用從政府計劃轉移到由私人保險公司支付的問題。Medicare和Medicaid的較低報銷率，給醫院和醫生增加了{{link-en|轉移成本|Cost-shifting}}的壓力，他們對相同的服務，卻向私人保險公司收取較高的費率，最終是醫療保險的費率受到影響。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.managedcaremag.com/archives/0612/0612.costshift.html|title=Confronting The Medicare Cost Shift|work=Managed Care Magazine|access-date=2007-06-28|date=December 2006|archive-date=2021-01-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210126105822/http://www.managedcaremag.com/archives/0612/0612.costshift.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>
 
2010年3月，[[麻薩諸塞州|麻薩諸塞州]]發布一份有關成本驅動因素的報告，稱他們的發現為"全美獨有"。<ref name="MassCostTrends">[http://www.mass.gov/dhcfp/costtrends Health Care Cost Trends]. Massachusetts Office of Health and Human Services. See [http://www.mass.gov/Eeohhs2/docs/dhcfp/cost_trend_docs/final_report_docs/appendix_b_ag_report.pdf Appendix B: Preliminary Report of the Massachusetts Attorney General (PDF)] {{Wayback|url=http://www.mass.gov/Eeohhs2/docs/dhcfp/cost_trend_docs/final_report_docs/appendix_b_ag_report.pdf |date=20100509003338 }}, pp. 1–2, for quote and summary.</ref>報告指出，醫療機構和保險公司是透過私下談判報銷率，因此，提供相同服務的各家機構，和保險公司之間的價格可能會有所不同，並且價格的變化不是根據護理的品質，而是市場的談判能力。這份報告還發現，是因為價格上漲，不是利用率增加，才造成過去幾年醫療費用支出的增長。<ref name="MassCostTrends" />
 
經濟學家{{link-en|埃里克·海蘭|Eric Helland}}和{{link-en|亞歷克斯·塔巴羅克|Alex Tabarrok}}兩位推測，美國醫療衛生費用的增長，在很大程度上是{{link-en|鮑莫爾效應|Baumol's cost disease}}的結果。由於醫療衛生是相對勞力密集型的，而服務部門的生產效率已經落後於商品生產部門（相對下，商品生產部門的薪資因此會較高），這些服務部門的薪資只好被拉高，以便留住這些勞動力。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mercatus.org/system/files/helland-tabarrok_why-are-the-prices-so-damn-high_v1.pdf|last1=Helland|first1=Eric|last2=Tabarrok|first2=Alex|name-list-format=vanc|title=Why Are the Prices So Damn High?|access-date=2019-05-26|date=May 2019|archive-date=2021-01-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210129172639/https://www.mercatus.org/system/files/helland-tabarrok_why-are-the-prices-so-damn-high_v1.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==監管與監督==
