美國的聯邦基金會在2014年所做的一項研究發現，美國的醫療體系是世界上最昂貴的，但與[[澳大利亞|澳大利亞]]、加拿大、法國、德國、荷蘭、紐西蘭、[[挪威|挪威]]、[[瑞典|瑞典]]、瑞士、和英國等在各方面做比較，幾乎都是敬陪末座。研究發現，美國在獲取、效率、和公平性三方面是倒數第二。研究資料的來源有取自[[患者|患者]]和[[初級照護|初級照護]]醫生的國際性調查，以及聯邦基金會、WHO，和OECD所提供的有關醫療衛生結果的資訊。<ref name=":12">{{Cite journal|date=2017-06-14|title=Mirror, Mirror 2017: International Comparison Reflects Flaws and Opportunities for Better U.S. Health Care|url=https://www.commonwealthfund.org/publications/fund-reports/2017/jul/mirror-mirror-2017-international-comparison-reflects-flaws-and|journal=|publisher=The Commonwealth Fund|volume=|pages=|doi=|via=|name-list-format=vanc|access-date=2020-09-04|archive-date=2020-03-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200330201719/https://www.commonwealthfund.org/publications/fund-reports/2017/jul/mirror-mirror-2017-international-comparison-reflects-flaws-and|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url = https://www.vox.com/2014/6/16/5812898/five-ways-the-american-health-care-system-is-literally-the-worst|title = Five ways the American health care system is literally the worst|last = Kliff|first = Sarah|name-list-format = vanc|date = 2014-06-16|work = Vox|access-date = 2014-06-17|archive-date = 2021-01-13|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210113215255/https://www.vox.com/2014/6/16/5812898/five-ways-the-american-health-care-system-is-literally-the-worst|dead-url = no}}</ref>
 
截至2017年，美國的預期壽命是80.00歲，在世界排名第43位。<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/rankorder/2102rank.html#us |work=The World Factbook |publisher=Cia.gov |date= |access-date=2018-12-14 |title=Country Comparison: Life Expectancy at Birth |archive-date=2016-01-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160120024054/https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/rankorder/2102rank.html#us |dead-url=no }}</ref>中央情報局的《[[世界概況|世界概況]]》資料，顯示美國的嬰兒死亡率（5.80/1,000活產嬰兒），依照數字由高到低，在225國家/地區之中是排名第170位（等於在低死亡率群組裡面排名第55名）。<ref name="infant_mortality_by_country">{{cite web|url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/rankorder/2091rank.html#us|work=The World Factbook|date=|publisher=Cia.gov|access-date=2018-12-14|title=Country Comparison: Infant Mortality Rate|archive-date=2018-02-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180207062332/https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/rankorder/2091rank.html#us|dead-url=no}}</ref>美國人接受癌症篩檢的比率也比其他已開發國家高，並且是在OECD國家中，使用MRI掃描和CT掃描比率最高的國家。<ref name="Atlas">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0qExi2-3m5IC|title=In excellent health : setting the record straight on America's health care and charting a path for future reform|first=Scott W.|last=Atlas|name-list-format=vanc|publisher=Hoover Institution Press, Stanford University|year=2011|isbn=978-0-8179-1444-8|location=Stanford, California|pages=199–205|access-date=2020-09-04|archive-date=2020-12-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201207144329/https://books.google.com/books?id=0qExi2-3m5IC|dead-url=no}}</ref>
 
對在1997年至2003年期間所做的一項研究發現，美國在可預防的死亡人數的下降速度，比其他18個工業化國家來的緩慢。<ref>Ellen Nolte and C. Martin McKee, [http://content.healthaffairs.org/cgi/content/abstract/27/1/58?ijkey=05uD000683MNE&keytype=ref&siteid=healthaff "Measuring the Health of Nations: Updating an Earlier Analysis,"], [[Health_Affairs|Health Affairs]], January 8, 2008, Volume 98</ref>一項在 2008年所做的研究發現，如果美國的醫療體系如同法國、日本、或澳大利亞那麼有效，那麼美國每年的死亡人數就可減少101,000人。<ref name="reuters1">{{cite news| title = France best, U.S. worst in preventable death ranking| first = Will| last = Dunham| name-list-style = vanc| url = https://www.reuters.com/article/us-deaths-rankings-idUSN0765165020080108| work = Reuters| date = January 8, 2008| access-date = April 3, 2012| archive-date = 2021-10-08| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20211008043356/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-deaths-rankings-idUSN0765165020080108| dead-url = no}}</ref>經濟學家{{link-en|安妮·凱斯|Anne Case}}和[[安格斯·迪頓|安格斯·迪頓]]在2020年所做的一項研究，他們認為美國"花費巨額資金，卻在[[西方世界|西方世界]]中有最糟糕的健康結果。"<ref>{{cite book |last1=Case |first1=Anne |last2=Deaton |first2=Angus |date=2020 |title=Deaths of Despair and the Future of Capitalism |url=https://www.google.com/books/edition/Deaths_of_Despair_and_the_Future_of_Capi/bHK0DwAAQBAJ?hl=en&gbpv=1&pg=PA9&printsec=frontcover |location= |publisher=[[Princeton_University_Press|Princeton University Press]] |pages=9–10 |isbn=978-0691190785 |access-date=2020-09-04 |archive-date=2020-12-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201207144320/https://www.google.com/books/edition/Deaths_of_Despair_and_the_Future_of_Capi/bHK0DwAAQBAJ?hl=en&gbpv=1&pg=PA9&printsec=frontcover |dead-url=no }}</ref>
 
OECD發現，美國在{{link-en|潛在減壽年數|years of potential life lost}}（YPLL）方面排名不佳，這是一項統計指標，用於衡量在70歲以下，可以透過醫療衛生挽救的生命年限。在OECD有相關數據的國家中，美國在婦女的醫療衛生方面名列倒數第三（僅好過[[墨西哥|墨西哥]]和[[匈牙利|匈牙利]]），在男子中名列倒數第五（僅好過[[斯洛伐克|斯洛伐克]]和[[波蘭|波蘭]]等國家）。
  
最近的研究發現，因為收入和地理位置的不同，會發生人們的預期壽命差距越來越大的情況。一項在2008年由政府資助的研究發現，1983年至1999年，有180個縣的女性和11個縣的男性的預期壽命下降，大部分的下降發生在[[密西西比河|密西西比河]]沿岸的[[美國深南部|美國深南部]]、[[阿巴拉契亞山脈|阿巴拉契亞山脈]]、還有在南部平原和[[德克薩斯州|德克薩斯州]]。最高的年齡差異是男性高達三年，女性高達六年。年齡差異是源自於貧富和教育程度之間的差異，但源自男女性別以及種族之間的則在縮小。<ref name="Ezzati2008">{{cite journal | vauthors = Ezzati M, Friedman AB, Kulkarni SC, Murray CJ | title = The reversal of fortunes: trends in county mortality and cross-county mortality disparities in the United States | journal = PLOS Medicine | volume = 5 | issue = 4 | pages = e66 | date = April 2008 | pmid = 18433290 | pmc = 2323303 | doi = 10.1371/journal.pmed.0050066 | lay-url = https://www.nytimes.com/2008/04/27/weekinreview/27sack.html | editor1-last = Novotny | editor1-first = Thomas | access-date = 2020-09-04 | archive-date = 2020-12-07 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201207144256/https://www.nytimes.com/2008/04/27/weekinreview/27sack.html | dead-url = no }}</ref> 另一項研究發現，1993年至2001年，年齡在25至64歲之間的成年人中，受過良好教育的人與教育程度不高的之間的死亡率差距顯著擴大。作者推測，這些差異可能是由[[吸菸|吸菸]]，肥胖症，和高血壓等危險因素所造成。<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Jemal A, Ward E, Anderson RN, Murray T, Thun MJ | title = Widening of socioeconomic inequalities in U.S. death rates, 1993-2001 | journal = PLOS ONE | volume = 3 | issue = 5 | pages = e2181 | date = May 2008 | pmid = 18478119 | pmc = 2367434 | doi = 10.1371/journal.pone.0002181 | bibcode = 2008PLoSO...3.2181J }}</ref>
 
[[美國國家科學研究委員會|美國國家科學研究委員會]]預測，在2011年，由於吸菸而導致的死亡人數會急劇下降，預期壽命因而可改善；研究還顯示，預期壽命差異中的五分之一至三分之一是由於肥胖症所造成，美國有世界上最嚴重的的肥胖症問題，而且還在加劇中。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/section/healthy-living |title=Healthy Living |work=The Huffington Post |date= |access-date=2016-12-01 |archive-date=2018-09-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180930083146/https://www.huffingtonpost.com/section/healthy-living |dead-url=no }}</ref>從1990年至1994年，在31個國家/地區診斷出的[[乳癌|乳癌]]、大腸癌、和[[前列腺癌|前列腺癌]]得到的資料，美國人在乳癌和前列腺癌有最高的[[五年存活率|五年存活率]]，但是美國黑人，無論男女，在這兩項的存活率確是顯著的低很多。<ref>{{cite web |last=Doheny |first=Kathleen |name-list-format=vanc |date=2008-07-16 |title=Cancer survival rates vary by country. Study shows U.S., Japan, and France have highest cancer survival rates |website=[[WebMD|WebMD]] |url=http://www.webmd.com/cancer/news/20080716/cancer-survival-rates-vary-by-country |accessdate=2020-09-04 |archive-date=2020-11-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201129133445/https://www.webmd.com/cancer/news/20080716/cancer-survival-rates-vary-by-country |dead-url=no }}<br />{{cite journal | vauthors = Coleman MP, Quaresma M, Berrino F, Lutz JM, De Angelis R, Capocaccia R, Baili P, Rachet B, Gatta G, Hakulinen T, Micheli A, Sant M, Weir HK, Elwood JM, Tsukuma H, Koifman S, E Silva GA, Francisci S, Santaquilani M, Verdecchia A, Storm HH, Young JL | display-authors = 6 | title = Cancer survival in five continents: a worldwide population-based study (CONCORD) | journal = The Lancet. Oncology | volume = 9 | issue = 8 | pages = 730–56 | date = August 2008 | pmid = 18639491 | doi = 10.1016/S1470-2045(08)70179-7 | doi-access = free }}<br />In the CONCORD study, [[Cuba|Cuba]] had the highest five-year relative survival rates for breast cancer and for colorectal cancer in women, but problems with data quality might have led to over-estimations.</ref>
 
在美國，對於醫療衛生的辯論涉及的是：雖然花了大錢，但是在獲取、效率、和品質方面所存在的問題。在2000年WHO的資料裡面，美國醫療系統在回應效率是排名第1，但總體績效只排名第37，整體健康水準排名第72（資料中有191國）。<ref name="photius.com">[http://www.photius.com/rankings/who_world_health_ranks.html World Health Organization assesses the world's health system] {{Wayback|url=http://www.photius.com/rankings/who_world_health_ranks.html |date=20210126184007 }}. Press Release WHO/44 21 June 2000.</ref><ref name="who.int">{{cite web|url=http://www.who.int/whr/2000/en/annex01_en.pdf|title=The World Health Report 2000 : Annex Table 1 Health system attainment and performance in all Member States, ranked by eight measures, estimates for 1997|website=Who.int|access-date=2016-12-01|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112031211/https://www.who.int/whr/2000/en/annex01_en.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>自由市場擁護者{{link-en|戴維·格拉澤|David Gratzer}}對於WHO的研究的批評是，因為"財務貢獻的公平性"被用作評估的項目，而美國有高額的人均私人​​醫療費用，或者是高額的自付醫療費用，排名因此被降低。<ref name="fmc">[[David_Gratzer|David Gratzer]], [http://www.freemarketcure.com/whynotgovhc.php Why Isn't Government Health Care The Answer?] {{Wayback|url=http://www.freemarketcure.com/whynotgovhc.php |date=20090312071328 }}, ''Free Market Cure'', July 16, 2007</ref>這項WHO的研究因為並未包含公眾的滿意度作為評估的項目，而受到刊在{{link-en|健康事務|health affairs}}一篇文章的批評。<ref name="Blendon">Robert J. Blendon, Minah Kim and John M. Benson, [http://content.healthaffairs.org/cgi/reprint/20/3/10.pdf "The Public Versus The World Health Organization On Health System Performance,"] {{Wayback|url=http://content.healthaffairs.org/cgi/reprint/20/3/10.pdf |date=20090326093056 }} Health Affairs, May/June 2001</ref>研究發現，WHO的衛生系統排名與使用民眾的滿意度之間的關聯甚小。<ref name="Blendon" />獲得WHO給予最高評分的[[義大利|義大利]]和[[西班牙|西班牙]]等國家，它們的公民反給予不良的評分，而獲得低分的[[丹麥|丹麥]]和[[芬蘭|芬蘭]]，國民對於醫療系統表示滿意的比率最高。<ref name="Blendon" />但是WHO的工作人員說，他們的分析確實表達出系統，針對民眾的預期的"回應效率"，並認為這是表達消費者滿意度的一種良好指標。<ref>Christopher J.L. Murray, Kei Kawabata, and Nicole Valentine, [http://content.healthaffairs.org/cgi/reprint/20/3/21 "People's Experience Versus People's Expectations"] {{Wayback|url=http://content.healthaffairs.org/cgi/reprint/20/3/21 |date=20040619143202 }}, Health Affairs, May/June 2001</ref>此外，患者滿意度與醫療衛生的利用、支出、和結果之間的關係相當複雜，尚無法明確做定義。<ref name=Fenton2012>{{cite journal | vauthors = Fenton JJ, Jerant AF, Bertakis KD, Franks P | title = The cost of satisfaction: a national study of patient satisfaction, health care utilization, expenditures, and mortality | journal = Archives of Internal Medicine | volume = 172 | issue = 5 | pages = 405–11 | date = March 2012 | pmid = 22331982 | doi = 10.1001/archinternmed.2011.1662 | url = http://archinte.jamanetwork.com/data/Journals/INTEMED/22610/iiq120001_405_411.pdf | doi-access = free | access-date = 2020-09-04 | archive-date = 2017-09-22 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170922002014/http://archinte.jamanetwork.com/data/journals/intemed/22610/iiq120001_405_411.pdf | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Maratt|first1=Jennifer K.|last2=Kerr|first2=Eve A.|last3=Klamerus|first3=Mandi L.|last4=Lohman|first4=Shannon E.|last5=Froehlich|first5=Whit|last6=Bhatia|first6=R. Sacha|last7=Saini|first7=Sameer D.|date=2019|title=Measures Used to Assess the Impact of Interventions to Reduce Low-Value Care: a Systematic Review|url= |journal=Journal of General Internal Medicine|language=en|volume=34|issue=9|pages=1857–1864|doi=10.1007/s11606-019-05069-5|issn=0884-8734|pmc=6712188|pmid=31250366}}</ref>
 
{{link-en|兒童發展基金會|Foundation for Child Development}}於2008年4月發布的一份報告，在對1994年至2006年之間的研究，發現美國兒童的健康狀況是好壞參半，1-4歲兒童的死亡率下降三分之一，高血中鉛濃度的兒童下降84％。在懷孕期間吸菸的母親比例也有所下降。另一方面，肥胖症和[[低出生體重兒|低出生體重兒]]的百分比都在增加。作者指出，出生時體重過輕的嬰兒的增加，或可歸因於婦女推遲生育時間和增加使用生育藥物的緣故。<ref>Donna St. George, [https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/04/23/AR2008042303666.html "For Children, a Better Beginning,"] {{Wayback|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/04/23/AR2008042303666.html |date=20201207144435 }} ''[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]]'', April 24, 2008</ref><ref>Kenneth C. Land, Project Coordinator, [http://www.fcd-us.org/usr_doc/EarlyChildhoodWell-BeingReport.pdf "2008 Special Focus Report: Trends in Infancy/Early Childhood and Middle Childhood Well-Being, 1994–2006,"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.fcd-us.org/usr_doc/EarlyChildhoodWell-BeingReport.pdf |date=20090326093058 }} The Foundation for Child Development Child and Youth Well-Being Index (CWI) Project, Foundation for Child Development (FCD), April 24, 2008</ref>
 
在13個已開發國家中，美國各別在2009年和2013年，其人口在14種類別的加權藥物使用量排名第三。所選擇的藥物是因為在過去的十年中，用它們作治療的疾病具有較高的發病率、患病率、和/或死亡率、產生嚴重的長期發病率、也產生高昂的費用支出、並且在預防或治療方面都有重大進展。研究指出，做跨境用藥情況比較有很大的困難度。<ref>{{cite web|last1=Office of health Economics|title=International Comparison of Medicines Usage: Quantitative Analysis|url=http://www.abpi.org.uk/our-work/library/industry/Documents/meds_usage.pdf|publisher=Association of the British Pharmaceutical Industry|access-date=2015-07-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151111181650/http://www.abpi.org.uk/our-work/library/industry/Documents/meds_usage.pdf|archive-date=2015-11-11|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

