==系統效率和公平性==
{{link-en|醫療衛生效率|Health care efficiency}}的差異可導致結果的差異。例如，達特茅斯醫療衛生地圖集（The Dartmouth Atlas of Health Care）報告說，在過去的20多年中，美國醫療資源分配和使用方式的顯著變化，也導致顯著的成果變化。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dartmouthatlas.org/index.shtm |title=Dartmouth Atlas of Health Care |website=Dartmouthatlas.org |date=2015-12-30 |access-date=2016-12-01 |archive-date=2010-04-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100414014020/http://www.dartmouthatlas.org/index.shtm |dead-url=no }}</ref>醫師在不同地區工作的意願，會隨著當地的收入，以及當地所提供的便利設施而變化，在美國，這種情況會因為醫師短缺，特別是那些初級照護醫師的供應量而更加惡化。如果實施《PPACA》，將會產生對初級照護醫生的額外需求，而現在他們實際上已經是供應不足（特別是在經濟狀況不佳的地區）。訓練出更多的醫生還需要花費好幾年的時間才能達成。<ref name=NYT72812>{{cite news|title=Doctor Shortage Likely to Worsen With Health Law|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/07/29/health/policy/too-few-doctors-in-many-us-communities.html|access-date=2012-07-29|newspaper=The New York Times|date=2012-07-28|last1=Lowrey|first1=Annie|first2=Robert|last2=Pear|name-list-format=vanc|archive-date=2020-12-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201207144449/https://www.nytimes.com/2012/07/29/health/policy/too-few-doctors-in-many-us-communities.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>
 
像{{link-en|價值流程圖|value stream mapping}}的[[精益生產|精益生產]]技術可幫助辨識，並隨後減輕與醫療衛生成本相關的浪費。<ref name="GJMR_Gill2012">{{cite journal | vauthors = Gill PS |title= Application of Value Stream Mapping to Eliminate Waste in an Emergency Room |journal= Global Journal of Medical Research  |volume=12 |year=2012 |issue=6 |pages=51–56 |url=http://dstats.net/download/http://globaljournals.org/GJMR_Volume12/8-Application-of-Value-Stream-Mapping.pdf}}</ref>其他的工具，例如[[失效模式與影響分析|失效模式與影響分析]]（FMEA）和[[石川圖|魚骨圖]]，也被用來提高服務的效率。<ref name="MC_Gill2013">{{cite journal|vauthors=Gill PS|title=Five Product Engineering Methods That Can Be Applied to Health Care Management|journal=Managed Care|volume=3|year=2013|pages=21–26|url=http://www.managedcaremag.com/archives/1303/1303.engineering.html|access-date=2020-09-04|archive-date=2015-09-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150911235956/http://www.managedcaremag.com/archives/1303/1303.engineering.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>
  
===效率===
====可預防的死亡====
在2010年，[[冠狀動脈疾病|冠狀動脈疾病]]、[[肺癌|肺癌]]、[[中風|中風]]、[[慢性阻塞性肺病|慢性阻塞性肺病]]、和交通事故，在美國造成最多的生命年損失<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.healthknowledge.org.uk/public-health-textbook/research-methods/1a-epidemiology/years-lost-life |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2020-09-04 |archive-date=2021-01-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210130174254/https://www.healthknowledge.org.uk/public-health-textbook/research-methods/1a-epidemiology/years-lost-life |dead-url=no }}</ref>。[[下背痛|下背痛]]、[[重性抑鬱疾患|抑鬱症]]、{{link-en|肌肉骨骼疾病|musculoskeletal disorder}}、頸部疼痛、和[[焦慮|焦慮]]是造成最多的殘疾生命年損失原因。危害最大的危險因素是不良飲食、吸菸、肥胖症、高血壓、[[高血糖|高血糖]]、缺乏運動、和飲酒。[[阿茲海默症|阿茲海默症]]、[[物質濫用|藥物濫用]]、[[腎病變|腎臟病]]、癌症、以及跌倒，是造成1990年人均{{link-en|年齡調整| age adjustment}}生命損失年最多的原因。<ref name=Murray2013 />
 
在1990年至2010年之間，OECD的34個國家/地區之中，美國的年齡調整死亡率從第18位降至第27位。在年齡調整生命年損失，美國從第23名跌至第 28名。出生時的預期壽命從第20名下降到第27名。{{link-en|健康生命年| Healthy Life Years}}從第14名降至第26名。<ref name=Murray2013>{{cite journal | vauthors = Murray CJ, Atkinson C, Bhalla K, Birbeck G, Burstein R, Chou D, etal | title = The state of US health, 1990-2010: burden of diseases, injuries, and risk factors | journal = JAMA | volume = 310 | issue = 6 | pages = 591–608 | date = August 2013 | pmid = 23842577 | pmc = 5436627 | doi = 10.1001/jama.2013.13805 | url = http://jama.jamanetwork.com/data/Journals/JAMA/0/joi130037.pdf | access-date = 2020-09-04 | archive-date = 2020-04-09 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200409130309/https://jamanetwork.com/journals/JAMA/articlepdf/1710486/joi130037.pdf | dead-url = no }}</ref>
 
根據2009年由{{link-en|支持全民醫療衛生計劃醫生團體|Physicians for a National Health Program}}（一個支持單一支付者付款系統的遊說團體）的聯合創始人在[[哈佛醫學院|哈佛醫學院]]所做的一項研究，在《{{link-en|美國公共衛生雜誌|American Journal of Public Health}}》上發表，報告指出，缺乏醫療保險會導致每年有近45,000的超額可預防的死亡。<ref name="Harvard Gazette">{{cite web | first = David | last = Cecere | name-list-format = vanc | date = 2009-09-17 | url = http://news.harvard.edu/gazette/story/2009/09/new-study-finds-45000-deaths-annually-linked-to-lack-of-health-coverage/ | title = New study finds 45,000 deaths annually linked to lack of health coverage | work = [[Harvard_Gazette|Harvard Gazette]] | access-date = 2013-08-27 | archive-date = 2021-01-30 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210130220814/https://news.harvard.edu/gazette/story/2009/09/new-study-finds-45000-deaths-annually-linked-to-lack-of-health-coverage/ | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="Wilper 2009">{{cite journal | vauthors = Wilper AP, Woolhandler S, Lasser KE, McCormick D, Bor DH, Himmelstein DU | title = Health insurance and mortality in US adults | url = https://archive.org/details/sim_american-journal-of-public-health_2009-12_99_12/page/2289 | journal = American Journal of Public Health | volume = 99 | issue = 12 | pages = 2289–95 | date = December 2009 | pmid = 19762659 | pmc = 2775760 | doi = 10.2105/AJPH.2008.157685 }}</ref>自那時以來由於未保險人數從2009年的約4,600萬增加到2012年的4,900萬，這種死亡人數已增長到每年約48,000人。<ref name=uninsureddeaths>{{cite web |vauthors= Woolhandler S |date= 2012-09-12 |title= Despite slight drop in uninsured, last year's figure points to 48,000 preventable deaths |publisher= Physicians for a National Health Program |url= http://www.pnhp.org/news/2012/september/despite-slight-drop-in-uninsured-last-year%E2%80%99s-figure-points-to-48000-preventable- |access-date= 2012-09-26 |display-authors= etal |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20120924021844/http://www.pnhp.org/news/2012/september/despite-slight-drop-in-uninsured-last-year%E2%80%99s-figure-points-to-48000-preventable- |archive-date= 2012-09-24 |url-status= dead |dead-url= no }}</ref>經濟學家{{link-en|約翰·古德曼|John C. Goodman}}對這個團體的方法論的批評是，它未研究死亡原因，也未追踪保險狀態隨時間（包括死亡時間）的變化。<ref name="Goodman">{{cite web|url=http://healthaffairs.org/blog/2009/09/21/does-lack-of-insurance-cause-premature-death/|title=Does Lack Of Insurance Cause Premature Death?|last=Goodman|first=John|name-list-format=vanc|date=2009-09-21|publisher=Health Affairs|access-date=2012-07-05|archive-date=2017-08-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170806131737/http://healthaffairs.org/blog/2009/09/21/does-lack-of-insurance-cause-premature-death/|dead-url=no}}</ref>
 
前[[比爾·柯林頓|柯林頓]]總統政策顧問{{link-en|理查德·克羅尼克|Richard Kronick}}在2009年作的一項研究，發表在《{{link-en|醫療保健服務研究|Health Services Research}}》雜誌上。研究發現，在控制某些風險因素之後，並無因未投保而導致死亡率的上升。<ref name="Kronick">{{cite journal|vauthors=Kronick R|date=August 2009|title=Health insurance coverage and mortality revisited|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_health-services-research_2009-08_44_4/page/1211|journal=Health Services Research|volume=44|issue=4|pages=1211–31|doi=10.1111/j.1475-6773.2009.00973.x|pmc=2739025|pmid=19453392}}<!--|access-date=August 15, 2014--></ref>
 
====物有所值====
一項在2000年發表在健康政策雜誌《健康事務》上，有關國際醫療衛生支出水準的研究發現，美國在醫療衛生上的支出比OECD中的任何其他國家都要多很多，而在大多方面，美國在服務的利用低於OECD的中位數。這項研究的作者的結論是，美國為醫療服務所付出的價格要比其他地方高得多。<ref name="Prices Stupid">Gerard F. Anderson, Uwe E. Reinhardt, Peter S. Hussey and Varduhi Petrosyan, [http://content.healthaffairs.org/cgi/content/abstract/22/3/89 "It's The Prices, Stupid: Why The United States Is So Different From Other Countries"] {{Wayback|url=http://content.healthaffairs.org/cgi/content/abstract/22/3/89 |date=20101123032837 }}, ''Health Affairs'', Volume 22, Number 3, May/June 2003. Retrieved February 27, 2008.</ref>雖然按GDP排名，少於美國的19個富裕國家的費用花不到美國的一半，但它們自1970年以來，國民的預期壽命都比美國多約6年。<ref name=Kenworthy2011 />
 
====延遲就診和增加使用急診服務====
沒有保險的美國人不太可能獲得定期醫療衛生，以及用到預防的服務。他們更有可能會延遲就醫，從而導致更多的醫療緊急情況，這比平日持續治療糖尿病和高血壓等所花的費用要高很多。[[美國醫學會雜誌|美國醫學會雜誌]]（JAMA）於2007年發表的一項研究，結論是在意外傷害發生，或者新的慢性疾病發作之後，未保險的人比有保險的接受醫療服務的可能性更低。未保險人在受傷後，沒接受到後續護理建議的可能性是有保險的人的兩倍，對於罹患新的慢性病者來說，情況類似。<ref name="pmid17356028">{{cite journal | vauthors = Hadley J | title = Insurance coverage, medical care use, and short-term health changes following an unintentional injury or the onset of a chronic condition | journal = JAMA | volume = 297 | issue = 10 | pages = 1073–84 | date = March 2007 | pmid = 17356028 | doi = 10.1001/jama.297.10.1073 | doi-access = free }}</ref>沒有保險的患者去醫院急診室的可能性是有保險者的兩倍。讓本來該用於處理真正緊急狀況的急診室，去處理較次要的緊急狀況，急診系統的負擔因而加重。<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cdc.gov/nchs/data/ad/ad388.pdf |title=Advance Data From Vital and Health Statistics No. 388 |website=Cdc.gov |date=2007-06-28 |access-date=2016-12-01 |archive-date=2020-10-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201017145019/https://www.cdc.gov/nchs/data/ad/ad388.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>
 
2008年，[[美國癌症協會|美國癌症協會]]的研究人員發現，沒有私人保險者（包括未受到Medicaid覆蓋的人）相較於擁有私人保險的人，更有可能被診斷出患有晚期的癌症。<ref name="Halpern2008">{{cite journal | vauthors = Halpern MT, Ward EM, Pavluck AL, Schrag NM, Bian J, Chen AY | title = Association of insurance status and ethnicity with cancer stage at diagnosis for 12 cancer sites: a retrospective analysis | journal = The Lancet. Oncology | volume = 9 | issue = 3 | pages = 222–31 | date = March 2008 | pmid = 18282806 | pmc =  | doi = 10.1016/S1470-2045(08)70032-9 }} Lay summary: [https://www.nytimes.com/2008/02/18/health/18cancer.html?_r=1&adxnnl=1&oref=slogin&adxnnlx=1203443524-1XOu0YisWP8MKgZnPMWtbQ Study Finds Cancer Diagnosis Linked to Insurance] {{Wayback|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2008/02/18/health/18cancer.html?_r=1&adxnnl=1&oref=slogin&adxnnlx=1203443524-1XOu0YisWP8MKgZnPMWtbQ |date=20201207144454 }}, ''New York Times''.</ref>
 
====醫療機構做法差異====
根據患者利用的不同醫療機構，患者受到的治療可能會有很大的差異。研究顯示，某些具有成本效益的治療方法並未經常被使用，而有些服務則有被過度使用的情況。[[不必要的醫療照顧|不必要的醫療照顧]]會把成本拉高，並可能導致患者產生不必要的焦慮。<ref>{{cite web |first = Valerie |last = Ulene |name-list-format = vanc |url = http://www.latimes.com/features/printedition/health/la-he-themd5-2008may05,0,2608989.story |title = Care that goes too far |work = [[Los_Angeles_Times|Los Angeles Times]] |date = 2008-05-05 |accessdate = 2020-09-04 |archive-date = 2008-06-13 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20080613221100/http://www.latimes.com/features/printedition/health/la-he-themd5-2008may05,0,2608989.story |dead-url = no }}</ref>處方藥的使用因地理區域而異。<ref>Emily Cox, Doug Mager, Ed Weisbart, [http://www.express-scripts.com/ourcompany/news/outcomesresearch/onlinepublications/study/geoVariationTrends.pdf "Geographic Variation Trends in Prescription Use: 2000 to 2006,"][[Express_Scripts|Express Scripts]], January 2008 {{Wayback|url=http://www.express-scripts.com/ourcompany/news/outcomesresearch/onlinepublications/study/geoVariationTrends.pdf |date=20080227072600 }}</ref>過度使用醫療福利是種[[道德風險|道德風險]]–有保險的人會更傾向多消費。
 
醫療系統試圖透過分擔共付額和自負額之類的策略，來消除這種過度使用的問題。如果患者必須要承擔更大的財務負擔，他們只會在有必要時，才去利用醫療衛生服務。根據蘭德公司所做的醫療保險實驗，共保額費率較高的人，比較低的人會少用醫療衛生服務。實驗的結論是，較少利用到護理通常不會造成[[社會福利|社會福利]]的損失，但是，對於較貧窮和容易生病的人群而言，必定會產生負面影響。這些患者被迫放棄必要的[[預防醫學|預防措施]]來省錢，延誤小病被早期發現，而發生後續更昂貴的治療。預防性護理少做的結果，昂貴的急診次數反而增加，使患者在財務上受害。在美國，這種不良循環隨之增加。更多昂貴的療程，導致更高的成本。<ref>[http://www.dartmouthatlas.org/topics/effective_care.pdf "Effective Care,"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.dartmouthatlas.org/topics/effective_care.pdf |date=20080216012730 }} The Dartmouth Atlas of Health Care, January 15, 2007</ref><ref>Laurence C. Baker, Elliott S. Fisher, and [[John_Wennberg|John E. Wennberg]], [http://content.healthaffairs.org/cgi/reprint/hlthaff.27.2.w123v1 "Variations In Hospital Resource Use For Medicare And Privately Insured Populations In California,"] {{Wayback|url=http://content.healthaffairs.org/cgi/reprint/hlthaff.27.2.w123v1 |date=20090513080518 }} Health Affairs web exclusive, February 2008</ref>
 
一項研究發現，在患者生命的最後兩年中，在Medicare方面的支出有明顯的地域差異。這些支出與每個地區擁有的醫院容量相關。高額支出，未必能讓患者的壽命更長。<ref name=DartmouthAtlas2008>John E. Wennberg, Elliott S. Fisher, David C. Goodman, and Jonathan S. Skinner, [http://www.dartmouthatlas.org/atlases/2008_Chronic_Care_Atlas.pdf "Tracking the Care of Patients with Severe Chronic Illness: the Dartmouth Atlas of Health Care 2008."] {{Wayback|url=http://www.dartmouthatlas.org/atlases/2008_Chronic_Care_Atlas.pdf |date=20081029000748 }} [[The_Dartmouth_Institute_for_Health_Policy_and_Clinical_Practice|The Dartmouth Institute for Health Policy and Clinical Practice]], May 2008, {{ISBN|978-0-9815862-0-5}} ([http://www.dartmouthatlas.org/atlases/2008_Atlas_Exec_Summ.pdf Executive Summary] {{Wayback|url=http://www.dartmouthatlas.org/atlases/2008_Atlas_Exec_Summ.pdf |date=20080408231441 }})</ref><ref>[http://www.kaisernetwork.org/daily_reports/rep_index.cfm?DR_ID=51385 "Medicare: End-of-Life Hospital Spending for Medicare Beneficiaries With Chronic Health Conditions Varies Widely, Study Finds,"]{{dead link|date=October 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} Kaiser Daily Health Policy Report, [[Kaiser_Family_Foundation|Kaiser Family Foundation]], April 7, 2008</ref>

====機構間對護理協調====
初級照護的醫生通常是大多數患者最先碰到的醫事人員，但是在美國分散的醫療體系中，許多患者及其醫療機構之間會有護理協調方面的問題。例如{{link-en|哈里斯民意調查|Harris Interactive}} 對加州醫師的調查發現：

*十分之四的醫生回應說，在過去的12個月中，他們的患者在護理協調方面遇到問題。
*超過60％的醫生回應說，他們的患者"有時"或"經常"要花漫長時間，等待診斷測試的結果。 
*約有20％的醫生回應說，由於無法在約好的就診時間找到測試的結果，患者只好重做一次。<ref>California HealthCare Foundation, [http://www.chcf.org/topics/view.cfm?itemid=133466 "Uncoordinated Care: A Survey of Physician and Patient Experience"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.chcf.org/topics/view.cfm?itemid=133466 |date=20080214013651 }}, Harris Interactive. 2007. Retrieved March 20, 2008.</ref>
 
根據《[[紐約時報|紐約時報]]》上的一篇文章，醫生與患者之間的關係正惡化中。<ref name="NYTJuly2008">Tare Parker-Pople, [https://www.nytimes.com/2008/07/29/health/29well.html?scp=1&sq=doctor%20and%20patient%20now%20at%20odds&st=cse "Well: Doctor and Patient, Now at Odds,"] {{Wayback|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2008/07/29/health/29well.html?scp=1&sq=doctor%20and%20patient%20now%20at%20odds&st=cse |date=20201128081637 }} ''[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]'', July 29, 2008</ref> [[約翰·霍普金斯大學|約翰·霍普金斯大學]]所做的一項研究發現，約有四分之一的患者認為他們的醫生讓他們曝露於不必要的風險，而根據諸如自助書籍和網絡文章之類的[[軼事證據|傳聞證據]]顯示，患者的沮喪感是有提高。醫患之間關係惡化的可能因素，包括有當前的醫師訓練系統以及醫患之間對醫療運作看法的差異。醫生可能會專注在做診斷和治療，而患者可能是更關心自身的健康，和希望醫生願意聆聽他們的敘述。<ref name="NYTJuly2008" />

許多初級照護醫生不再在醫院看病人，而是由住院醫生（hospitalist，請參考{{link-en|醫院醫學|hospital medicine}}）做這樣的事。<ref>Hospitalists and the family physician [http://www.aafp.org/afp/980800ap/edit.html] {{Wayback|url=http://www.aafp.org/afp/980800ap/edit.html |date=20111026025031 }} by Bruce Bagley, M.D.; American Family Physician</ref>醫療保險公司有時要求使用住院醫生，作為節省成本的方式，有些初級照護醫生對此表示不滿。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.acpinternist.org/archives/1999/05/hosps.htm |title=Use of mandatory hospitalists blasted, ACP Observer May 99 |website=Acpinternist.org |date=1999-02-16 |access-date=2016-12-01 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019223115/http://www.acpinternist.org/archives/1999/05/hosps.htm |archive-date=2016-10-19 |dead-url=no }}</ref>
 
====行政管理費用====
截至2017年，美國有907家醫療保險公司，<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iii.org/fact-statistic/facts-statistics-industry-overview|title=Facts + Statistics: Industry overview {{!}} III|website=www.iii.org|access-date=2019-06-24|archive-date=2021-01-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210129065203/https://www.iii.org/fact-statistic/facts-statistics-industry-overview|dead-url=no}}</ref>排名在前10名的公司約佔總收入的53％，排名前100名的佔總收入的95％。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.treasury.gov/initiatives/fio/reports-and-notices/Documents/2018_FIO_Annual_Report.pdf|title=Annual Report on the Insurance Industry (September 2018)|publisher=FEDERAL INSURANCE OFFICE, U.S. DEPARTMENT OF THE TREASURY|access-date=|archive-date=2020-10-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201020013007/https://www.treasury.gov/initiatives/fio/reports-and-notices/Documents/2018_FIO_Annual_Report.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>{{Rp|70}}數量龐大的保險公司，所產生的行政管理費用，遠超過國有化的[[單一支付者醫療衛生系統|單一支付者醫療衛生系統]]（例如加拿大的）。加拿大的行政管理費用估計約只有美國的一半。<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Woolhandler S, Campbell T, Himmelstein DU | title = Costs of health care administration in the United States and Canada | journal = The New England Journal of Medicine | volume = 349 | issue = 8 | pages = 768–75 | date = August 2003 | pmid = 12930930 | doi = 10.1056/NEJMsa022033 | s2cid = 2313231 | url = https://semanticscholar.org/paper/39dd21f8f5d96a1fb3defdc661de26742a20a589 }}</ref>
 
《美國健康保險計劃》估計，在過去40年中，行政管理費用平均約佔所收保費的12％，這種費用用在醫療管理、護士求助熱線、以及與醫療機構談判費用折扣之上，而非用在理賠事務。<ref>Jeff Lemieux, [http://www.ahipresearch.org/pdfs/Administrative_Costs_030705.pdf "Perspective: Administrative Costs of Private Health Insurance Plans"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.ahipresearch.org/pdfs/Administrative_Costs_030705.pdf |date=20071128170000 }}, [[America's_Health_Insurance_Plans|America's Health Insurance Plans]], 2005</ref>
 
{{link-en|藍十字與藍盾協會|Blue Cross and Blue Shield Association}}（BCBSA）於2003年發布的一項研究還發現，醫療保險公司的行政管理費用約佔保費收入的11％至12％，而BCBSA的行政管理費用平均要比一般商業保險低一點。<ref>[http://www.bcbs.com/betterknowledge/cost/Cost_Admin030703.pdf "Understanding Health Plan Administrative Costs"], [[Blue_Cross_and_Blue_Shield_Association|Blue Cross Blue Shield Association]], 2003 {{Wayback|url=http://www.bcbs.com/betterknowledge/cost/Cost_Admin030703.pdf |date=20071026063247 }}</ref>從1998年到2003年，保險公司的這項費用從保費的13％下降到12％。行政費用增幅最大的是在客戶服務和資訊科技，而降幅最大的是在為醫療機構服務、訂約、和一般管理。<ref>{{cite report | first1 = Kent J. | last1 = Sacia | first2 = Robert H. | last2 = Dobson | name-list-format = vanc | title = Health Plan Administrative Cost Trends | publisher = [[Blue_Cross_and_Blue_Shield_Association|BlueCross BlueShield Association]] | work = Milliman USA | date = 20 February 2003 }}</ref>管理顧問公司[[麥肯錫|麥肯錫]]估計，在"醫療行政管理和保險"上的超支，估計佔超額支出總額（在2003年為4,770億美元）的21％。<ref>{{cite news | url=https://economix.blogs.nytimes.com/2008/11/21/why-does-us-health-care-cost-so-much-part-ii-indefensible-administrative-costs/ | work=The New York Times | title=Why Does U.S. Health Care Cost So Much? (Part II: Indefensible Administrative Costs) | first=Uwe E. | last=Reinhardt | name-list-format=vanc | date=2008-11-21 | access-date=2010-05-04 | archive-date=2021-01-01 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210101222442/https://economix.blogs.nytimes.com/2008/11/21/why-does-us-health-care-cost-so-much-part-ii-indefensible-administrative-costs/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>
  
根據CBO在2008年發布的一份報告，私人保險的行政管理費用約佔保費的12％。私人保險計劃之間的行政管理費用的差異，主要由規模經濟所產生。大型雇主的保險行政管理成本最低。較小公司的類似費用在保費的佔比增加，而在個人購買的保險佔比最高。<ref>[[Congressional_Budget_Office|U.S. Congressional Budget Office]], [http://www.cbo.gov/sites/default/files/cbofiles/ftpdocs/99xx/doc9924/12-18-keyissues.pdf ''Key Issues in Analyzing Major Health Insurance Proposals''] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cbo.gov/sites/default/files/cbofiles/ftpdocs/99xx/doc9924/12-18-keyissues.pdf |date=20201118085421 }}, December 2008</ref>BCBSA在2009年發表的一項研究發現，所有商業醫療保險產品的平均行政管理費用成本，在2008年的保費中佔到9.2％。<ref name="Sherlock 2009" />這種費用佔小型團體保險保費的11.1％，在個人市場中則佔16.4％。<ref name="Sherlock 2009">{{cite web|first = Douglas B.|last = Sherlock|name-list-format = vanc|url = http://s3.amazonaws.com/zanran_storage/www.bcbs.com/ContentPages/25302966.pdf|title = Administrative Expenses of Health Plans|publisher = [[Blue_Cross_and_Blue_Shield_Association|Blue Cross Blue Shield Association]]|date = 2009|via = s3.amazonaws.com|accessdate = 2020-09-04|archive-date = 2014-02-14|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140214234248/http://s3.amazonaws.com/zanran_storage/www.bcbs.com/ContentPages/25302966.pdf|dead-url = no}}</ref>
 
一項關於帳單和保險相關（ billing and insurance-related，BIR）成本的研究，發現這種成本不僅由保險公司，而且還有醫生和醫院一起承擔，在加州的急診醫療架構中，保險公司、醫生、和醫院的BIR成本佔私人保險保費的20-22％ 。.<ref name="pmid16284038">{{cite journal | vauthors = Kahn JG, Kronick R, Kreger M, Gans DN | title = The cost of health insurance administration in California: estimates for insurers, physicians, and hospitals | journal = Health Affairs | volume = 24 | issue = 6 | pages = 1629–39 | year = 2005 | pmid = 16284038 | doi = 10.1377/hlthaff.24.6.1629 | doi-access = free }}</ref>
 
====長期生活療養機構====
截至2014年，根據一份報告<ref>{{cite journal |pmc = 6376502|year = 2019|last1 = Weech-Maldonado|first1 = R.|last2 = Pradhan|first2 = R.|last3 = Dayama|first3 = N.|last4 = Lord|first4 = J.|last5 = Gupta|first5 = S.|title = Nursing Home Quality and Financial Performance: Is There a Business Case for Quality?|journal = Inquiry : A Journal of Medical Care Organization, Provision and Financing|volume = 56|pages = 0046958018825191|doi = 10.1177/0046958018825191|pmid = 30739511}}</ref> ，{{link-en|註冊護士|registered nurse}}的工作技能越高，對於療養機構的財務成本就越低。隨著老年人口的增加，他們住進長期生活機構，就需要更多護理，讓財務成本上升加速。根據在2010年所做的研究，<ref>{{cite journal|pmc = 2763425|year = 2009|last1 = Stewart|first1 = K. A.|last2 = Grabowski|first2 = D. C.|last3 = Lakdawalla|first3 = D. N.|title = Annual expenditures for nursing home care: Private and public payer price growth, 1977–2004|url = https://archive.org/details/sim_medical-care_2009-03_47_3/page/295|journal = Medical Care|volume = 47|issue = 3|pages = 295–301|doi = 10.1097/MLR.0b013e3181893f8e|pmid = 19194339}}</ref>每年這類患者的自付費用增長7.5％，而Medicare費用也由於這種因素而每年增長 6.7％。住在這些機構中的患者中有40％是自付費用，Medicare為在這兒的老年人提供某些護理費用。<ref>{{cite journal |pmc = 2763425|year = 2009|last1 = Stewart|first1 = K. A.|last2 = Grabowski|first2 = D. C.|last3 = Lakdawalla|first3 = D. N.|title = Annual expenditures for nursing home care: Private and public payer price growth, 1977–2004|url = https://archive.org/details/sim_medical-care_2009-03_47_3/page/295|journal = Medical Care|volume = 47|issue = 3|pages = 295–301|doi = 10.1097/MLR.0b013e3181893f8e|pmid = 19194339}}</ref>
 
===第三方支付問題和消費者驅動的保險===
大多數美國人透過保險方式來支付醫療服務費用，因為消費者僅直接支付最終費用的一部分，這種情況可能會把消費者的動機給扭曲。<ref name=just />有關醫療服務的價格資訊不足，也會把激勵措施給扭曲。<ref name=just />代表被保險人付款的保險公司會與醫療機構協商，他們有時會使用政府設定的價格（例如Medicaid帳單價格）作參考。<ref name=just />
 
這種推理引發人們呼籲，希望對於保險制度做改革，以建立一個由{{link-en|消費者驅動的醫療保健|Consumer-driven healthcare}}系統，讓消費者支付更多的自付費用。<ref name="Scandlen2005">{{cite journal | vauthors = Scandlen G | title = Consumer-driven health care: just a tweak or a revolution? | journal = Health Affairs | volume = 24 | issue = 6 | pages = 1554–8 | year = 2005 | pmid = 16284028 | pmc =  | doi = 10.1377/hlthaff.24.6.1554 | doi-access = free }}</ref>2003年，《{{link-en|醫療保險處方藥，改良和現代化法案|Medicare Prescription Drug, Improvement, and Modernization Act}}》通過，這項法案鼓勵消費者選擇高自付費用的醫療計劃，和設立健康儲蓄帳戶。在2019年10月，[[科羅拉多州|科羅拉多州]]提案通過私人保險公司來經營公共醫療衛生的方案，而首先就要承擔這種費用的壓力。到2022年，公共選項的保費被吹捧成會便宜9％至18％。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.denverpost.com/2019/10/07/colorado-public-insurance-option-draft/|title=Colorado proposes running public health care option through private insurers|date=2019-10-07|website=The Denver Post|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-21|archive-date=2020-12-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201207144657/https://www.denverpost.com/2019/10/07/colorado-public-insurance-option-draft/|dead-url=no}}</ref>
 
===公平性===
