===藥物效力和安全性===
{{see also|{{link-en|美國治療用藥的法規|Regulation of therapeutic goods in the United States}}}}
 
FDA<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fda.gov/AboutFDA/WhatWeDo/WhatFDARegulates/default.htm|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090604111232/https://www.fda.gov/AboutFDA/WhatWeDo/WhatFDARegulates/default.htm|url-status=dead|archive-date=2009-06-04|title=What FDA Regulates|date=2009-06-04|accessdate=2020-09-04|dead-url=no}}</ref>是一個負責人類和動物用藥的安全性和有效性的主要機構。它還負責確保把有關藥物的資訊，準確和翔實地公佈給公眾。FDA審查並批准藥品，並設定藥品的標籤、藥品的標準、和醫療設備的製造標準。它也負責制定[[輻射|輻射]]和[[超聲波|超聲波]]設備的性能標準。
  
與藥物安全性有關的，更具爭議性的問題之一，是執行機構[[免於起訴|免於起訴]]的地位。在2004年，FDA推翻一項聯邦政策，認為FDA的上市前核准（FDA premarket approval）優於根據州法律對醫療器械提出的大多數損害賠償的要求。2008年，最高法院在 {{link-en|Riegel訴Medtronic案|Riegel v. Medtronic}}中把這一點確認。<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Glantz LH, Annas GJ | title = The FDA, preemption, and the Supreme Court | journal = The New England Journal of Medicine | volume = 358 | issue = 18 | pages = 1883–5 | date = May 2008 | pmid = 18450601 | doi = 10.1056/NEJMp0802108 }}</ref>
  
2006年6月30日，FDA的一項裁定生效，把訴訟保護範圍擴展到藥品製造商，即使藥廠為求藥物批准，向FDA提交詐欺性的臨床試驗數據，也可受到保護。這讓使用不良藥品而受害的患者求訴無門。2007年，眾議院對FDA的裁定表達反對，但參議院未採取任何行動。2009年3月4日，美國最高法院作出一項重要判決，在{{link-en|惠氏藥品訴Levine案|Wyeth v. Levine}}中，法院判定聯邦豁免不能超越州一級的訴訟權，而必須"為受害的消費者提供適當的救濟。"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.oyez.org/cases/2000-2009/2008/2008_06_1249/|title=''Wyeth v. Levine''|work=Oyez|publisher=Chicago-Kent College of Law at Illinois Tech|date=n.d.|accessdate=2020-09-04|archive-date=2015-09-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924111356/http://www.oyez.org/cases/2000-2009/2008/2008_06_1249/|dead-url=no}}</ref>2009年6月，HHS部長[[凱瑟琳·西貝利厄斯|凱瑟琳·西貝利厄斯]]，根據{{link-en|公眾安妥和緊急預備法案|Public Readiness and Emergency Preparedness Act}}簽署一項命令，宣布與{{link-en|2009年豬流感疫苗|2009 flu pandemic vaccines}}管理有關的緊急衛生事件中，把訴訟保護範圍擴展到疫苗生產商，以及聯邦官員。<ref>{{USFedReg|74|30294}}, [[Federal_Register|Federal Register]]: June 25, 2009 (Volume 74, Number 121), pp. 30294–97.</ref><ref>[http://www.flu.gov/professional/federal/vaccineliability.html Coverage Under the Public Readiness and Emergency Preparedness (PREP) Act for H1N1 Vaccination] {{Wayback|url=http://www.flu.gov/professional/federal/vaccineliability.html |date=20111108182243 }} Flu.gov, retrieved November 11, 2009</ref>

===處方藥價格===
{{main|美國的處方藥價格}}
 
在1990年代，處方藥的價格成為美國政治中的一個主要議題，因為許多新藥的價格呈現倍增狀態，而且許多公民發現政府和保險公司都不會負擔此類藥物的費用。美國的人均藥品支出高於任何其他國家，雖然這種支出在醫療衛生總費用中所佔的比率不大（13％），而OECD國家的平均佔比為 18％（ 2003年的數字）。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.oecd.org/dataoecd/15/23/34970246.pdf |title=OECD Health Data, How Does the United States Compare |publisher=[[Organisation_for_Economic_Co-operation_and_Development|Organisation for Economic Co-operation and Development]] |access-date=2007-04-14 |archive-date=2015-09-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924090158/http://www.oecd.org/dataoecd/15/23/34970246.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>另一項研究發現，在1990年到2016年間，美國處方藥的價格增加277%，同期的英國僅增加57%，加拿大增加13%，而在法國及日本，價格是下跌的。<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Stelzner|first=Mark Joseph|last2=Nam|first2=Daniel Taekmin|date=2020-08-11|title=The big cost of big medicine – calculating the rent in private healthcare|url=https://doi.org/10.1080/00346764.2020.1804607|journal=Review of Social Economy|volume=0|issue=0|pages=1–23|doi=10.1080/00346764.2020.1804607|issn=0034-6764}}</ref>個人的自付費用中約有25％是用在處方藥之上。<ref name="pmid15451969">{{cite journal | vauthors = Heffler S, Smith S, Keehan S, Clemens MK, Zezza M, Truffer C | title = Health spending projections through 2013 | journal = Health Affairs | volume = Suppl Web Exclusives | issue =  | pages = W4–79–93 | year = 2004 | pmid = 15451969 | doi = 10.1377/hlthaff.w4.79 | url = http://content.healthaffairs.org/cgi/pmidlookup?view=long&pmid=15451969 }}</ref>
 
美國政府的立場（透過[[美國貿易代表處|美國貿易代表處]]）是美國消費者透過提高的藥品價格去補貼美國的藥廠，因為這些藥廠的產品無法從其他國家賺取足夠的利潤（這些國家運用大宗購買力的優勢，積極協商出優惠的價格）。<ref>See the summary of the official U.S. position in the [http://www.ustr.gov/assets/Trade_Sectors/Intellectual_Property/Special_301_Public_Submissions_2008/asset_upload_file109_14495.pdf "Pharmaceutical Research and Manufacturers of America (PhRMA) Special 301 Submission of 2008"], February 11, 2008, 10–20. {{Wayback|url=http://www.ustr.gov/assets/Trade_Sectors/Intellectual_Property/Special_301_Public_Submissions_2008/asset_upload_file109_14495.pdf |date=20081121034643 }}</ref>美國的立場（與美國藥品研發與製造廠的主要遊說立場一致）是這些國家/地區的政府是搭上美國消費者補貼美國藥廠的便車。
 
因此，這些外國政府應該放鬆對市場的管制，或者提高他們國內稅負，希望能直接透過把差價支付給美國政府，或者是美國藥廠，以便公平地補償美國消費者。反過來，美國藥廠就能夠繼續生產創新藥物，同時降低在美國的價格。目前美國政府在採購藥品時，可就一些藥品價格作談判，但由於2003年通過的《醫療保險處方藥，改良和現代化法案》，這項法案禁止Medicare就藥品價格作談判。民主黨人指控這項規定僅僅是為了允許製藥產業從Medicare計劃中牟取暴利。<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2006/11/06/business/06drug.html?pagewanted=all | work=The New York Times | title=As Drug Prices Climb, Democrats Find Fault With Medicare Plan | first=Alex | last=Berenson | name-list-format=vanc | date=2006-11-06 | access-date=2010-05-04 | archive-date=2020-12-07 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201207144822/https://www.nytimes.com/2006/11/06/business/06drug.html?pagewanted=all | dead-url=no }}</ref>
 
====製藥公司的影響====
美國和紐西蘭是世界上僅有的兩個允許直接{{link-en|向消費者作處方藥廣告|Direct-to-consumer advertising}}的國家。2015年，美國醫學會呼籲禁止這樣的直接廣告方式，因為這種做法與藥品價格上漲有關聯。<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.ama-assn.org/press-center/press-releases/ama-calls-ban-dtc-ads-prescription-drugs-and-medical-devices | title=AMA calls for ban on direct to consumer advertising of prescription drugs and medical devices | date=2015-11-17 | author=AMA | accessdate=2020-09-04 | archive-date=2020-12-07 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201207144829/https://www.ama-assn.org/press-center/press-releases/ama-calls-ban-dtc-ads-prescription-drugs-and-medical-devices | dead-url=no }}</ref>雖說如此，有其他證據指出，直接對消費者作廣告有一些好處，例如，鼓勵患者去看醫生，診斷罕見疾病，以及消除與某些疾病相關的污名。<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Ventola CL | title = Direct-to-Consumer Pharmaceutical Advertising: Therapeutic or Toxic? | journal = P & T | volume = 36 | issue = 10 | pages = 669–84 | date = October 2011 | pmid = 22346300 | pmc = 3278148 }}</ref>
 
在2009年制定PPACA的時候，藥廠被要求支持這項立法，交換條件是不允許從國外進口藥品到美國。<ref>{{cite news | url=http://articles.latimes.com/2009/dec/16/nation/la-na-health-senate16-2009dec16 | work=Los Angeles Times | title=Senate healthcare bill advances with rejection of imported drugs | first1=Janet | last1=Hook | first2=Noam N. | last2=Levey | name-list-format=vanc | date=2009-12-16 | access-date=2010-05-04 | archive-date=2010-03-25 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100325093757/http://articles.latimes.com/2009/dec/16/nation/la-na-health-senate16-2009dec16 | dead-url=no }}</ref><!---so what? Need to follow this sentence with "critics believe that this fosters increased drug costs since drug companies are not subject to competition" or whatever--->

==醫療衛生改革的辯論==
{{main|美國醫療改革}}
 
在2010年進行重大醫療衛生改革之前的2008年，美國人對美國醫療系統的看法分歧。45％的人認為美國的制度最好，39％的人認為其他國家的制度比美國好。<ref>[http://www.hsph.harvard.edu/news/press-releases/2008-releases/republicans-democrats-disagree-us-health-care-system.html "Most Republicans Think the U.S. Health Care System is the Best in the World. Democrats Disagree.,"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.hsph.harvard.edu/news/press-releases/2008-releases/republicans-democrats-disagree-us-health-care-system.html |date=20120522101940 }} Press Release, [[Harvard_School_of_Public_Health|Harvard School of Public Health]] and [[Harris_Insights_&_Analytics|Harris Interactive]], March 20, 2008</ref><ref>[http://www.hsph.harvard.edu/news/press-releases/files/Topline__Best_HC_Havard_Harris.doc "Americans' Views on the U.S. Health Care System Compared to Other Countries,"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.hsph.harvard.edu/news/press-releases/files/Topline__Best_HC_Havard_Harris.doc |date=20080408231440 }} [[Harvard_School_of_Public_Health|Harvard School of Public Health]] and [[Harris_Insights_&_Analytics|Harris Interactive]], March 20, 2008</ref>

關於醫療衛生改革的歷史性辯論，大多圍繞在單一支付者醫療衛生系統，特別是指出提供醫療服務給無保險者，所存在的的隱性成本<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.iom.edu/Reports/2004/Insuring-Americas-Health-Principles-and-Recommendations.aspx|title=Insuring America's Health: Principles and Recommendations|work=[[Institute_of_Medicine|Institute of Medicine]] of the National Academies|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091019103757/http://www.iom.edu/Reports/2004/Insuring-Americas-Health-Principles-and-Recommendations.aspx|archive-date=2009-10-19|access-date=2007-10-27|dead-url=yes}}</ref>，而自由市場的擁護者則指出購買醫療保險屬於人民的自由選擇權利<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cato.org/research/articles/reynolds-021003.html|title=No Health Insurance? So What?|last=Reynolds|first=Alan|name-list-format=vanc|date=2002-10-03|work=The [[Cato_Institute|Cato Institute]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071014200629/http://cato.org/research/articles/reynolds-021003.html|archive-date=2007-10-14|url-status=dead|access-date=2007-10-27|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="CESR">Center for Economic and Social Rights. [http://cesr.org/ushealthright?PHPSESSID=91...a78f9969da61bd9 "The Right to Health in the United States of America: What Does it Mean?"]October 29, 2004. {{Wayback|url=http://cesr.org/ushealthright?PHPSESSID=91...a78f9969da61bd9 |date=20080214070649 }}</ref><ref name="Sade">{{cite journal | vauthors = Sade RM | title = Medical care as a right: a refutation | journal = The New England Journal of Medicine | volume = 285 | issue = 23 | pages = 1288–92 | date = December 1971 | pmid = 5113728 | doi = 10.1056/NEJM197112022852304 | url = http://www.aapsonline.org/brochures/sademcr.htm | access-date = 2020-09-04 | archive-date = 2020-11-22 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201122015445/https://www.aapsonline.org/brochures/sademcr.htm | dead-url = no }}</ref> ，以及指出政府干預所產生的意外後果（《{{link-en|1973年健康維護組織法|Health Maintenance Organization Act of 1973}}執行時發生的問題被引用》。<ref name="medca">{{cite web|url=http://www.reason.com/0411/fe.rb.mandatory.shtml|title=Mandatory Health Insurance Now! It will save private medicine – and spur medical innovation.|last=Bailey|first=Ronald|name-list-format=vanc|work=Reason Magazine|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060618023609/http://www.reason.com/0411/fe.rb.mandatory.shtml|archive-date=2006-06-18|access-date=2006-06-21|dead-url=no}}</ref>最終《PPACA》沒有採用單一支付者制度（這個制度有時候被稱為"{{link-en|社會化醫療衛生|Socialized medicine}}系統"） <ref>{{cite news|url=https://economix.blogs.nytimes.com/2009/05/08/what-is-socialized-medicine-a-taxonomy-of-health-care-systems/|title=What Is 'Socialized Medicine'?: A Taxonomy of Health Care Systems|last=Reinhardt|first=Uwe E.|name-list-format=vanc|date=2009-05-08|work=The New York Times|access-date=2010-05-04|archive-date=2020-12-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201207145004/https://economix.blogs.nytimes.com/2009/05/08/what-is-socialized-medicine-a-taxonomy-of-health-care-systems/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://voices.washingtonpost.com/ezra-klein/2009/06/health_reform_for_beginners_th_1.html|title=Health Reform for Beginners: The Difference Between Socialized Medicine, Single-Payer Health Care, and What We'll Be Getting|work=The Washington Post|access-date=2010-05-04|archive-date=2021-01-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210126185954/http://voices.washingtonpost.com/ezra-klein/2009/06/health_reform_for_beginners_th_1.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。
 
===《患者保護與平價醫療法案》（2010年）===
{{main|患者保護與平價醫療法案}}

《患者保護與平價醫療法案》（第111-148號公共法，PPACA）是一項醫療衛生改革法案，於2010年3月23日由歐巴馬總統簽署為法律。這項法案包括大量與醫療衛生相關的規定，其中大部分已於2014年生效，包括把收入在聯邦貧窮標線133％的人，擴大他們加入Medicaid的資格，<ref name="cnn_ref1">{{cite news |url= http://www.cnn.com/2010/HEALTH/03/25/health.care.law.basics/index.html |title= 5 key things to remember about health care reform |publisher= CNN |date= 2010-03-25 |first= Sabriya |last= Rice |name-list-format= vanc |accessdate= 2020-09-04 |archive-date= 2013-01-02 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20130102173326/http://www.cnn.com/2010/HEALTH/03/25/health.care.law.basics/index.html |dead-url= no }}</ref>補貼在聯邦貧窮標線400％的個人和家庭的保險費，並設定保費的上限，不超過受保者年度收入從2％到9.8％不等。<ref name=whitehouse>{{cite web |url= http://www.whitehouse.gov/health-care-meeting/proposal/whatsnew/affordability |title= Policies to Improve Affordability and Accountability |publisher= The White House |url-status= dead |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20121230013542/http://www.whitehouse.gov/health-care-meeting/proposal/whatsnew/affordability |archive-date= 2012-12-30 |accessdate= 2020-09-04 |dead-url= no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.csmonitor.com/USA/Politics/2010/0320/Health-care-reform-bill-101-Who-gets-subsidized-insurance|title=Health Care Reform Bill 101: Who gets subsidized insurance?|first=Peter|last=Grier|name-list-format=vanc|date=2010-03-20|work=[[The_Christian_Science_Monitor|The Christian Science Monitor]]|accessdate=2020-09-04|archive-date=2015-07-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150706014515/http://www.csmonitor.com/USA/Politics/2010/0320/Health-care-reform-bill-101-Who-gets-subsidized-insurance|dead-url=no}}</ref>PPACA是美國有史以來，首度發生對所有保單在個人（或家庭）的醫療費用的自付費用部分，設定年度上限。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bcbsm.com/index/health-insurance-help/faqs/topics/how-health-insurance-works/out-of-pocket-maximums.html |title=How do out-of-pocket maximums work? | FAQs |website=Bcbsm.com |date= |access-date=2016-12-01 |archive-date=2020-11-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201130182132/https://www.bcbsm.com/index/health-insurance-help/faqs/topics/how-health-insurance-works/out-of-pocket-maximums.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>
 
其他的條款包括用激勵措施，鼓勵企業提供醫療衛生福利，禁止因為申請人有[[既有身體狀況|既有身體狀況]]而拒絕承保，或發生拒絕理賠的情況，建立醫療衛生交易所，禁止保險公司設定年度理賠上限，和支持醫學研究。這些條款所需要的經費是透過各種稅收、收費、和節約措施來提供，例如針對高收入者的新Medicare稅、針對室內[[曬黑|曬黑]]的營業徵稅、把{{link-en|優惠醫療保險|Medicare Advantage}}計劃經費削減、把經費用以支持傳統 Medicare、以及對醫療器械和製藥公司徵收費用； <ref>Peter Grier, [http://www.csmonitor.com/USA/Politics/2010/0321/Health-care-reform-bill-101-Who-will-pay-for-reform Health care reform bill 101: Who will pay for reform?] {{Wayback|url=http://www.csmonitor.com/USA/Politics/2010/0321/Health-care-reform-bill-101-Who-will-pay-for-reform |date=20150706012138 }}, ''Christian Science Monitor'' (March 21, 2010).</ref>沒有取得醫療保險的公民也要繳稅（除非他們因為收入低下或另有原因而獲得豁免，請參考{{link-en|個人強制條款|individual mandate}}）。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.csmonitor.com/USA/Politics/2010/0319/Health-care-reform-bill-101-Who-must-buy-insurance |title=Health care reform bill 101: Who must buy insurance? |last=Grier |first=Peter |name-list-format=vanc |date=2010-03-19 |work=[[Christian_Science_Monitor|Christian Science Monitor]] |access-date=2010-04-07 |location=Washington, D.C. |archive-date=2010-04-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100405075157/http://www.csmonitor.com/USA/Politics/2010/0319/Health-care-reform-bill-101-Who-must-buy-insurance |dead-url=no }}</ref>
 
CBO估計，PPACA實施的淨結果（包括{{link-en|2010年醫療衛生與教育調節法案|Health Care and Education Reconciliation Act of 2010}}在內）可為聯邦赤字在頭一個十年減少1,430億美元。<ref>Congressional Budget Office, [http://www.cbo.gov/doc.cfm?index=11379&type=1 Cost Estimates for H.R. 4872, Reconciliation Act of 2010 (Final Health Care Legislation)] (March 20, 2010).</ref> 但是，兩個月後，CBO承認最初的估計漏列1,150億元的經費。此外，CBO估計，雖然根據《PPACA》，2016年小型和大型企業醫療保險計劃的預計人均保費將比不採用的低100美元，但個人購買醫療保險計劃的保費會增加1,900美元。<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Manchikanti|first=Laxmaiah|name-list-format=vanc|date=January 2011|title=Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act of 2010: Reforming the Health Care Reform for the New Decade|url=https://www.monroecollege.edu/uploadedFiles/_Site_Assets/PDF/2011.14.E35.E67.pdf|journal=Pain Physician|volume=14|issue=1|pages=E35–E67|pmid=21267047|access-date=2020-09-04|archive-date=2019-04-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190412063911/https://www.monroecollege.edu/uploadedFiles/_Site_Assets/PDF/2011.14.E35.E67.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>
 
《PPACA》的首度個公開登記加入階段從2013年10月開始。在此之前，美國全國獲得醫療衛生服務，和保險覆蓋率的趨勢都在惡化中。一項針對美國成年人的大規模全國性調查發現，在登記加入的頭兩個階段結束之後，自我報告的保險覆蓋率、健康狀況、和獲得護理的機會有顯著改善。此外，參與Medicaid擴張的州與沒參與的州相比，在低收入成年人獲得保險覆蓋的比率要高很多。<ref name=":32">{{cite journal | vauthors = Sommers BD, Gunja MZ, Finegold K, Musco T | title = Changes in Self-reported Insurance Coverage, Access to Care, and Health Under the Affordable Care Act | journal = JAMA | volume = 314 | issue = 4 | pages = 366–74 | date = July 2015 | pmid = 26219054 | doi = 10.1001/jama.2015.8421 | doi-access = free }}</ref>但是Medicaid與私人保險之間確實存有差異。有Medicaid覆蓋的人往往在自我報告時說他們的健康狀況尚好或較差，而不是像有私人保險的人報告說健康狀況良好或非常好。<ref name="pmid15055833">{{cite journal | vauthors = Hadley J, Holahan J | title = Is health care spending higher under Medicaid or private insurance? | journal = Inquiry | volume = 40 | issue = 4 | pages = 323–42 | date = 2003 | pmid = 15055833 | doi = 10.5034/inquiryjrnl_40.4.323 | doi-access = free }}</ref>
 
2017年12月22日，[[唐納·川普|川普]]總統簽署《 [[2017年減稅與就業法案|2017年減稅與就業法案]]》成為法律。在這項法案的最終版本中，把PPACA中的{{le|個人強制條款|individual mandate}}（也稱個人強制納保，條款要求個人和公司為自己和僱員獲得醫療保險，否則會有罰則）廢除。由於原來有這項條款，每個人都必須獲得保險，創造更大的資金池，促成費用得以分擔，而把醫療費用加以控制。經濟學家認為，雖然他們之間對於影響程度的意見不一，但個人強制條款的廢除將導致更高的保費和更低的醫療保險登記加入比率。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/12/18/us/politics/tax-cut-obamacare-individual-mandate-repeal.html|title=Without the Insurance Mandate, Health Care's Future May Be in Doubt|last=Pear|first=Robert|name-list-format=vanc|date=2017-12-18|work=The New York Times|access-date=2018-02-28|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2017-12-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171224155456/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/12/18/us/politics/tax-cut-obamacare-individual-mandate-repeal.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>
 
2017年，眾議院通過由川普總統領導的新的共和黨醫療法案，即《[[2017年美國保健法案|2017年美國保健法案]]》（俗稱川普健保（Trumpcare））。《PPACA（歐巴馬健保）》和《川普健保》都提出減稅政策，讓美國人更容易負擔醫療保險。但是，每一項法案都以不同的方式去影響美國人。受川普總統計劃影響最大的人是年輕人、社會經濟地位較高的人、以及居住在城市地區的人。在20至30歲之間的年輕人，他們的醫療保險保費會下降。
 
在歐巴馬健保之下，具有較高社會經濟地位的個人，可享受到稅收減免的最高年收入是50,000美元，而根據川普的計劃，這一稅收減免的收入上限數字則增加到115,000美元。此外，城市地區的人們也可從歐巴馬健保計劃中受益，因為根據歐巴馬健保計劃，稅收抵免也是由當地發生的醫療費用所決定，川普健保並未考慮到這一點，而農村地區由於缺乏醫院和可用的服務，費用因此高甚多。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-39233010|title=Trump health bill: Winners and losers|date=2017-05-04|work=BBC News|access-date=2018-02-28|language=en-GB|archive-date=2021-01-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210127003501/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-39233010|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==移民醫療保險==
{{main|{{link-en|美國的移民醫療保險|Immigrant health care in the United States}}}}
 
在1998年，居住在美國的2,620萬外國移民中，有62.9％並未取得美國國籍。1997年，居住在美國的34.3％的非美國公民沒有醫療保險，而沒有醫療保險的美國本地居民佔比是14.2％。在取得美國國籍的那些移民之中，沒有保險的人佔18.5％，而沒有保險的非公民則有43.6％。在每個年齡段和收入組裡面，移民獲得醫療保險的可能性都較小。<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Carrasquillo O, Carrasquillo AI, Shea S | title = Health insurance coverage of immigrants living in the United States: differences by citizenship status and country of origin | url = https://archive.org/details/sim_american-journal-of-public-health_2000-06_90_6/page/917 | journal = American Journal of Public Health | volume = 90 | issue = 6 | pages = 917–23 | date = June 2000 | pmid = 10846509 | pmc = 1446276 | doi = 10.2105/AJPH.90.6.917 }}</ref>隨著最近的醫療衛生變化，許多具有不同移民身份的合法移民，現在都有資格獲得負擔得起的醫療保險。<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.healthcare.gov/immigration-status-and-the-marketplace/ |title=Find out what immigration statuses qualify for coverage in the Health Insurance Marketplace. |website=HealthCare.gov |date= |access-date=2016-12-01 |archive-date=2014-10-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141001174442/https://www.healthcare.gov/immigration-status-and-the-marketplace/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>
 
美國境內的非法移民無法獲得政府資助的醫療保險。雖然《PPACA》允許移民以折扣價獲得保險，但沒有美國公民身份的移民仍然不能。<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.visitorguard.com/obamacare-for-usa-visitors-and-immigrants/#greencard|title=Obamacare: Visitors, International students, immigrants & US citizens|date=2013-12-24|newspaper=VisitorGuard.com|language=en-US|access-date=2016-11-17|archive-date=2020-10-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201020210750/https://www.visitorguard.com/obamacare-for-usa-visitors-and-immigrants/#greencard|dead-url=no}}</ref>雖然諸如《PPACA》之類法案的政策是用在擴大醫療保險的覆蓋範圍，以改善在美國的難民的健康狀況，但不同的州所實施的保險計劃有所不同，導致州與州之間醫療衛生的獲取存有差距。<ref name="ooo">{{cite journal |last1=Agrawal |first1=Pooja |last2=Venkatesh |first2=Arjun Krishna |title=Refugee Resettlement Patterns and State-Level Health Care Insurance Access in the United States |journal=American Journal of Public Health |date=2016 |volume=106 |issue=4 |pages=662–663 |doi=10.2105/AJPH.2015.303017 |pmid=26890186 |pmc=4816078 |issn=0090-0036}}</ref>在美國，非法移民可以向社區中心或所謂的社會安全網機構（Safety Net Providers）<ref>https://www.healthaffairs.org/doi/full/10.1377/hlthaff.2011.1270</ref>尋求醫療協助，並透過[[按服務收費|按服務收費]]的機構取得服務，也能從私人醫療保險公司購買醫療保險。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.coveredca.com/individuals-and-families/getting-covered/immigrants/|title=Health Insurance for Immigrants {{!}} Covered California™|website=coveredca.com|access-date=2016-11-17|archive-date=2020-09-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200928143946/https://www.coveredca.com/individuals-and-families/getting-covered/immigrants/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Elvish|first=Emily|date=2020|title=Donald Trump has tested positive for coronavirus|url=https://happymag.tv/donald-trump-has-tested-positive-for-coronavirus/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201207145101/https://happymag.tv/donald-trump-has-tested-positive-for-coronavirus/|archive-date=2020-12-07|access-date=|website=|dead-url=no}}</ref>

